CategoryNode.description: Represents a tree of Solution categories.

CategoryNodeLocalization.description: When the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization, the CategoryNodeLocalization object provides the translation of the label of a solution category.

Change Set Operation Event Type.description: Change Set Operation events contain information from change set migrations.

ChangeRequest.description: Represents a decision to implement a formal request for a change (RFC).

ChangeRequestRelatedIssue.description: Represents a junction object that relates a ChangeRequest to an Incident or Problem due to a service failure.

ChangeRequestRelatedItem.description: Represents a junction object that relates a ChangeRequest to an Asset.

ChangeSetOperationEventLog.description: Change Set Operation events contain information from change set migrations.

ChannelObjectLinkingRule.description: Represents a rule for linking a channel interaction with an object (such as Lead or Contact).

ChannelProgram.description: Represents a channel program that vendors use to market and sell their products through channel partners.

ChannelProgramLevel.description: Represents a level, based on member experience, in a channel program.

ChannelProgramMember.description: Represents a partner who is a member of a channel program.

ChatterActivity.description: ChatterActivity represents the number of posts and comments made by a user and the number of comments and likes on posts and comments received by the same user.

ChatterAnswersActivity.description: Represents the reputation of a User in Chatter Answers zones.

ChatterAnswersReputationLevel.description: Represents a reputation level within a Chatter Answers zone.

ChatterConversation.description: Represents a private conversation in Chatter, consisting of messages that conversation members have sent or received.

ChatterConversationMember.description: Represents a member of a private conversation in Chatter. A member has either sent messages to or received messages from other conversation participants.

ChatterExtension.description: Represents a Rich Publisher App that’s integrated with the Chatter publisher.

ChatterExtensionConfig.description: Configuration for the Chatter extension for Experience Cloud sites.

ChatterMessage.description: Represents a message sent as part of a private conversation in Chatter.

Claim.description: Represents a warranty Claim submitted by a partner to a manufacturer, or a supplier recovery claim submitted by the manufacturer to a supplier.

Claim Case.description: A junction object that associates the Claim object with the Case object. You see this object only if you have enabled the Use Many-to-Many Relationships org pref.

ClaimCovPaymentAdjustment.description: Represents the amount increased or decreased on a claim coverage payment as adjustments such as deductibles, copays, or coinsurance when applied on a claimed amount.

ClaimCovReserveAdjustment.description: Represents the amount adjusted on a claim coverage reserve as the reserve is changed and payments are made.

ClaimCoverage.description: Represents a causal part in a defective asset that requires repair or replacement.

ClaimCoveragePaymentDetail.description: Represents the claim coverage amount that must be paid to a claimant for a part replaced or replaced or a labor service performed to rectify a causal part in a defective asset.

ClaimCoverageProdtProcDef.description: Represents the definition for custom configurations that's used for processing claim coverage payment details.

ClaimFinancialSettings.description: Represents the configuration settings for Insurance Claim Financial Services.

ClaimItem.description: Represents a defective asset that requires repair or replacement.

ClaimItemAttribute.description: Represents attributes for a claim item.

ClaimItemRelatedObject.description: Represents the relationship between a claim item and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on the claim item.

ClaimParticipant.description: A junction object that associates the Claim object with the Account object. This object represents the participants of a claim.

ClaimPaymentSummary.description: Represents the amount of money that's paid to a claimant or claim participant to cover a claim.

ClaimPayoutPlan.description: Represents the payout plan details for a claim, such as payment frequency, duration, and payouts.

ClaimRecovery.description: Represents a recovery of funds on an insurance claim through subrogation and salvage activities. Recovered amounts can come from a salvage company or through legal litigation or arbitration. Master-detail child object of Claim.

ClaimTeamMember.description: Represents a user who is a part of the claim team.

CleanEnergyProject.description: Represents information about a project that provides credits a company can purchase to claim clean energy usage.

ClientBrowser.description: Represents a cookie added to the browser upon login, and also includes information about the browser application where the cookie was inserted.

ClimateChgEmssnFincSummary.description: Represents the emissions and financial information that a company discloses as part of ESRS E1 - Climate change.

ClimateChgRiskOppSummary.description: Represents the climate-related risks and opportunities that a company discloses as part of ESRS E1 - Climate change.

ClinicalMeasure.description: Represents a structured and computable definition of a health-related measure for identifying care gaps. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

ClinicalMeasureCriteria.description: Represents a computable criteria of a health-related measure. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

ClinicalMeasureCriteriaGrp.description: Represents a group of computable criteria for a health-related measure. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

CodeSet.description: Represents various industry defined codes in the context of their systems and versions of those systems.

CodesetRelationship.description: Represents a relationship between a codeset and its related codeset. For example, a labor code associated with a fault code.

CollabDocumentMetric.description: Represents the engagement metrics for a Quip thread (document or spreadsheet) that’s linked to a Salesforce record.

CollabDocumentMetricRecord.description: Represents an association between a CollabDocumentMetric and a Salesforce record.

CollabTemplateMetric.description: Represents the engagement metrics for a Quip template.

CollabTemplateMetricRecord.description: Represents an association between a CollabTemplateMetric and a Salesforce record.

CollabUserEngagementMetric.description: Represents the user engagement metrics for a Quip thread in a Quip template or document.

CollabUserEngmtRecordLink.description: Represents an association between a CollabUserEngagementMetric and a Salesforce record.

CollaborationGroupMember.description: Represents a member of a Chatter group.

CollaborationGroupMemberRequest.description: Represents a request to join a private Chatter group.

CollaborationGroupRecord.description: Represents the records associated with Chatter groups.

CollaborationInvitation.description: Represents an invitation to join Chatter, either directly or through a group.

CollaborationRoom.description: Represents a collaboration room, which links Salesforce to a Slack channel used by applications with specific use cases, such as swarming or reporting.

ColorDefinition.description: Represents the color-related metadata for a custom tab.

CombinedAttachment.description: This read-only object contains all notes, attachments, Google Docs, documents uploaded to libraries in Salesforce CRM Content, and files added to Chatter that are associated with a record.

CommSubscription.description: Represents the subscription options for a specific communication.

CommSubscriptionChannelType.description: Represents the engagement channel through which you can reach a customer for a communication subscription.

CommSubscriptionConsent.description: Represents a customer’s consent to a communication subscription.

CommSubscriptionTiming.description: Represents a customer's timing preferences for receiving a communication subscription.

CommerceEntitlementBuyerGroup.description: Represents the entitlement policy for a buyer group.

CommerceEntitlementPolicy.description: Represents an entitlement policy, which determines what products and prices a user can see.

CommerceEntitlementPolicyShare.description: Represents the entitlement rule for sharing products and prices with users other than the owner.

CommerceEntitlementProduct.description: Represents the entitlement policy for a product.

CommissionSchedule.description: Represents a commission calculation and rate definition. Calculates commission values for a commissionable event.

CommissionScheduleAssignment.description: Represents the commission calculation applicable to a specific product or producer for one or multiple commissionable events.

Community (Zone).description: Represents a zone that contains Idea or Question objects.

Competency.description: Represents a skill, subject matter expertise, or behavior required for a job or role.

CompetencyRelatedObject.description: Represents a junction between competency and another object.

ComplaintCase.description: Represents the association between a public complaint and its corresponding case.

ComplaintParticipant.description: Represents a junction between a public complaint, and an account or a contact. This object stores the details of the participant who registers a complaint with the authorities. This participant could be the applicant, co-applicant, a household, or even a business account.

Composite API Event Type.description: Composite API events contain details about composite API requests.

Composite API Subrequest Event Type.description: Composite API subrequest events contain details about composite API subrequests.

ConcurApexLimitEventLog.description: Concurrent Apex Limit event logs contain information about long-running concurrent Apex requests in your org that Salesforce terminated after reaching your org’s concurrency limit. Requests with an established Apex context that execute for 5 seconds are counted towards your org’s limit of concurrent long-running requests. (Asynchronous requests don’t count towards the limit.) When the long-running requests exceed the org default limit, additional long-running requests are denied.

Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit Event.file: objects/C/Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit Event Type.json
Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit Event.description: Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit events contain information about long-running concurrent Apex requests in your org that Salesforce terminated after reaching your org’s concurrency limit. Requests with an established Apex context that execute for 5 seconds are counted towards your org’s limit of concurrent long-running requests. (Asynchronous requests don’t count towards the limit.) When the long-running requests exceed the org default limit, additional long-running requests are denied.

CondIntrctnHlthRskAdjFctr.description: Stores the risk adjustment factor for patients and members based on the set of interacting conditions they are diagnosed with and the status of their benefits eligibility.

ConferenceNumber.description: Holds the telephone number for an external event shown in the Salesforce Today feature in the Salesforce mobile app.

ConnectedApplication.description: Represents a connected app and its details; all fields are read-only.

Console Event Type.description: Console events contain information about the performance and use of Salesforce Consoles. The Console events are logged whenever a Console tab is opened with a sidebar component. Outside of that, when Console tabs are opened, a regular view record detail event is served just like in Salesforce Classic.

ConstituentRole.description: Contains information about roles associated with the individual.

Consumption Rate.description: Consumption rates describe the billing rate for a range of usage within a consumption schedule. All consumption schedules require at least one consumption rate in order to rate usage on a usage product.

Consumption Schedule.description: A consumption schedule organizes a set of consumption rates by which usage-based products are quoted and billed.

ContCalloutSummaryEventLog.description: Continuation Callout Summary events contain information about all of the asynchronous callouts performed during a transaction, their response status codes, execution times, and URL endpoint destinations.

Contact.description: Represents a contact, which is a person associated with an account.

ContactCenterChannel.description: Represents a junction object that relates a Bring Your Own Channel for Contact Center as a Service (CCaaS) messaging channel to a CallCenter object for Bring Your Own Channel for CCaaS. This object also represents the routing details for a voicemail configuration.

ContactCleanInfo.description: Stores the metadata Data.com Clean uses to determine a contact record’s clean status. Helps you automate the cleaning or related processing of contact records. ContactCleanInfo includes a number of bit vector fields.

ContactDailyMetric.description: Represents the daily engagement metrics for a contact.

ContactMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for a contact.

ContactOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a contact with a User other than the owner.

ContactPointAddress.description: Represents a contact’s billing or shipping address, which is associated with an individual or person account.

ContactPointConsent.description: Represents a customer's consent to be contacted via a specific contact point, such as an email address or phone number.

ContactPointEmail.description: Represents a contact’s email, which is associated with an individual or person account.

ContactPointPhone.description: Represents a contact’s phone number, which is associated with an individual or person account.

ContactPointTypeConsent.description: Represents consent for a contact point type, such as email or phone.

ContactProfile.description: Represents information about an individual, such as their ethnicity, citizenship, birth place, race, and so on.

ContactRequest.description: Represents a customer’s request for support to get back to them about an issue.

ContactRequestShare.description: Represents a list of access levels to a ContactRequest with an explanation of the access level.

ContactShare.description: Represents a list of access levels to a Contact along with an explanation of the access level. For example, if you have access to a record because you own it, the ContactAccessLevel is All and RowCause is Owner.

ContactSuggestionInsight.description: Represents a suggestion for a new contact record.

ContactTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Contact.

Content Distribution Event Type.description: Content Distribution events contain information about content distributions and deliveries to users.

Content Document Link Event Type.description: Content Document Link events contain sharing information for content documents.

Content Transfer Event Type.description: Content Transfer events contain information about content transfer events, such as downloads, uploads, and previews. This information includes events performed on files and attachments to records.

ContentAsset.description: Represents a Salesforce file that has been converted to an asset file in a custom app in Lightning Experience. Use asset files for org setup and configuration. Asset files can be packaged and referenced by other components.

ContentBody.description: Represents the body of a file in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files

ContentDistribution.description: Represents information about sharing a document externally.

ContentDistributionEventLog.description: Content Distribution events contain information about content distributions and deliveries to users.

ContentDistributionView.description: Represents information about views of a shared document.

ContentDocLinkEventLog.description: Content Document Link events contain sharing information for content documents.

ContentDocument.description: Represents a document that has been uploaded to a library in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files. This object is available in versions 17.0 and later for Salesforce CRM Content.

ContentDocumentHistory.description: Represents the history of a document.

ContentDocumentLink.description: Represents the link between a Salesforce CRM Content document, Salesforce file, or ContentNote and where it's shared. A file can be shared with other users, groups, records, and Salesforce CRM Content libraries.

ContentDocumentListViewMapping.description: Represents an association between a ListView and a Quip ContentDocument. Applies to Quip file types only. Maintains the mapping between a list view and Quip document when the list view is exported to a newly created Quip document.

ContentDocumentSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following or commenting on a file in a library.

ContentFolder.description: Represents a folder in a content library for adding files.

ContentFolderItem.description: Represents a file (ContentDocument) or folder (ContentFolder) that resides in a ContentFolder in a ContentWorkspace.

ContentFolderLink.description: Defines the association between a library and its root folder.

ContentFolderMember.description: Defines the association between a file and a folder.

ContentHubItem.description: Represents a file or folder in a Files Connect external data source, such as Microsoft SharePoint or OneDrive for Business.

ContentHubRepository.description: Represents a Files Connect external data source such as Microsoft SharePoint or OneDrive for Business.

ContentLink.description: Represents a reference object with information about its content source.

ContentNote.description: Represents a note created with the enhanced note taking tool, released in Winter ‘16.

ContentNotification.description: Represents a notification for a file.

ContentSource.description: Represents the data source that's referenced by an object.

ContentTagSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a tag on a file.

ContentTaxonomy.description: Represents a content taxonomy, which is used to classify and organize Salesforce CMS content. To create a hierarchy of terms in a content taxonomy, use this object in addition to the ContentTaxonomyTerm, ContentTaxonomyRelatedTerm, and ContentTaxonomyTermRelatedTerm objects.

ContentTaxonomyRelatedTerm.description: Represents the relationship between a term and the content taxonomy to which the term belongs.

ContentTaxonomyTerm.description: Represents a term in a content taxonomy. Terms describe what content is or how it's used, and they’re organized in parent-child relationships in the taxonomy hierarchy.

ContentTaxonomyTermRelatedTerm.description: Represents the relationship between two terms in a content taxonomy.

ContentTaxonomyTermRelationshipType.description: Represents the type of relationship between two terms in a content taxonomy.

ContentTransferEventLog.description: ContentTransferEventLog stores information about content transfer events, such as downloads, uploads, and previews. This information includes events performed on files and attachments to records.

ContentUserSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following another user.

ContentVersion.description: Represents a specific version of a document in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files.

ContentVersionComment.description: Represents a comment on a version of a file.

ContentVersionHistory.description: Represents the history of a specific version of a document.

ContentVersionRating.description: Represents a rating on a version of a file.

ContentWorkspaceDoc.description: Represents a link between a document and a public library in Salesforce CRM Content.

ContentWorkspaceMember.description: Represents a member of a content library.

ContentWorkspaceSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a library.

ContextMappingConfig.description: Represents the context mapping configurations for business process types.

ContextParamMap.description: Represents optional context data for a Conversation or a ConversationParticipant.

Continuation Callout Summary Event Type.description: Continuation Callout Summary events contain information about all of the asynchronous callouts performed during a transaction, their response status codes, execution times, and URL endpoint destinations.

Contract.description: Represents a contract (a business agreement) associated with an Account.

ContractContactRole.description: Represents the role that a Contact plays on a Contract.

ContractGroupPlan.description: Represents a set of plans as part of the contract between the insurance carrier and the group. This set of plans corresponds to the plans included in the quote (as Quote Line Items). Child object of Contract.

ContractGroupPlanGroupClass.description: Represents the association of a Contract Group Plan to a Group Class. Use this entity to define group classes and group class contributions at the contract group plan level.

ContractGrpPlanGrpClsAttr.description: Represents a view of the attributes selected for each contract group plan group class.

ContractLineItem.description: Represents a product covered by a service contract (customer support agreement).

ContractLineOutcome.description: Represents information on a contract line outcome’s captured data and other related parameters that are used when capturing data.

ContractLineOutcomeData.description: Represents the contract line outcome’s captured data. It stores the data that was captured between the contract line outcome’s start date and end date. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.

ContractPaymentAgreement.description: Stores information about the contract payment agreement associated with a contract.

ContractStatus.description: Represents the status of a Contract, such as Draft, InApproval, Activated, Terminated, or Expired.

ContractTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Contract.

ConvAnalysisSummary.description: Represents the information stored for each run or refresh of Sales Signals.

ConvAnalysisTopic.description: Represents a topic generated from the Sales Signals refresh or run. For example, a product experiencing issues due to high pricing could be a topic identified through the analysis of multiple calls.

ConvAnalysisTopicEntry.description: Represents a single entry under the ConvAnalysisTopic object. An entry represents a segment of a video or voice call that is associated with a conversation analysis topic.

ConvIntelligenceSignalRule.description: Represents a conversation intelligence signal rule.

ConvIntelligenceSignalSubRule.description: Represents a condition (subrule) within a conversation intelligence signal rule.

ConvMessageSendRequest.description: Represents a request to send a template-based messaging component to a series of messaging users in an enhanced messaging channel or Messaging for In-App.

Conversation.description: Represents a conversation between an end user and an agent.

ConversationApiLog.description: Logs of an API operation on a specific conversation object done using the Conversation Service API.

ConversationChannelDefinition.description: Represents a configurable definition of a conversation channel that’s implemented for Interaction Service for Bring Your Own Channel for Messaging and Bring Your Own Channel for CCaaS messaging channels.

ConversationContextEntry.description: Represents the context of a message or an event in the chat history between an agent and a messaging user.

ConversationEntry.description: Represents a message or event in a voice call or a standard or enhanced messaging session.

ConversationParticipant.description: Represents an active participant in a conversation. A new ConversationParticipant record is created each time a participant joins a conversation.

ConversationVendorInfo.description: This setup object connects the partner vendor system to the Service Cloud feature.

CorsWhitelistEntry.description: Represents an entry in the cross-origin resource sharing (CORS) allowlist. Origins included in the allowlist can request REST resources from that Salesforce org.

CostCenter.description: Represents the actual expenses that are compared to the budget.

Coupon.description: A coupon associated with a promotion.

CourseCreditTransferAppln.description: Represents the details of a course credit transfer application.

CourseOffering.description: Represents an instance of a training course with location and date details of training courses

CourseOfferingParticipant.description: Represents information about a student's enrollment in a Course Offering.

CourseOfferingPtcpResult.description: Represents the outcome of a student's participation in a course.

CourseOfferingRelationship.description: Represents a junction between a course offering and a related course offering.

CourseOfferingSchedule.description: Represents information about the schedule defined for a Course Offering.

CourseOfferingScheduleTmpl.description: Represents a template that can be used to define a course schedule.

CourseOfrgRubricCriterion.description: Represents an activity rubric criterion for a course offering.

CoverageBenefit.description: Represents the benefits provided to a covered member by a purchaser’s plan.

CoverageBenefitItem.description: Specific service covered by the insurance plan.

CoverageBenefitItemLimit.description: Allows you to track details associated with a specific benefit as it relates to expenditures, limits, coverage levels, eligibility, and exclusion.

CoverageType.description: Represents the type of coverage, such as liability, earthquake, or collision damage. You see this object only if you have enabled the Access Master List of Coverage Types org pref.

CrbnCreditAlloc.description: Represents information about how the carbon credits are allocated by an organization to offset their emissions.

CrbnCreditAllocItem.description: Represents information about carbon credit allocation and emissions related to each emission activity.

CrbnCreditDistribution.description: Represents a junction between the sustainability credit and carbon credit allocation objects. To offset emissions for carbon credit allocation items, specify the emissions activity on this junction object.

CrbnCreditProject.description: Represents information about the environmental project that generates carbon credits by removing greenhouse gasses or preventing a certain quantity of greenhouse gasses from being released.

CrbnEmssnScopeAlloc.description: Represents the allocation of fuel consumption for different scope emissions. For an energy use record, tCO₂e is calculated and the results are classified as either Scope 1, Scope 2, or Scope 3 emission values. Each individual fuel type has its own scope allocation record. To put the tCO2e result in the correct scope, the energy use record points to the scope allocation record.

CrbnEmssnScopeAllocVal.description: Represents the scope allocation by fuel type.

CreditMemo.description: Represents a document that is used to reduce the amount that a buyer owes a seller under the terms of an earlier invoice.

CreditMemoAddressGroup.description: Stores the buyer's address information, which is used to determine the amount of tax to credit to a buyer when a credit memo is issued.

CreditMemoInvApplication.description: Represents an amount applied from a credit memo to an invoice.

CreditMemoLine.description: Represents product, service, adjustment, or tax line items that were included in a credit memo.

Crisis.description: Represents a major crisis event that affects an Employee in an InternalOrganizationUnit.

CronJobDetail.description: Contains details about the associated scheduled job, such as the job’s name and type.

CronTrigger.description: Contains schedule information for a scheduled job. CronTrigger is similar to a cron job on UNIX systems. This object is available in API version 17.0 and later.

CryptoProdCatgWalletGroup.description: Specifies if CryptoWalletGroup is in the allowlist or airdrop for the ProductCategory. A custom object between ProductCategory and CryptoWalletGroup adding the CryptoWalletGroup to allowlist or airdrop.

CspViolationEventLog.description: CSP violation events capture details about blocked resource requests from Lightning Experience pages based on your content security policy (CSP).

CurrencyType.description: Represents the currencies used by an organization for which the multicurrency feature is enabled.

CustExpIntlTransfSetup.description: Stores information for different data sources that are processed for customer insights. This object is available in API version 65.0 and later.

CustodyChainEntry.description: Represents information about an entry or event in the chain of custody.

CustodyItem.description: Represents information about an item in the custody chain.

CustodyItemRelation.description: Represents the relationship between a custody item and the context in which it’s held. For example, a custody item related to a case or case proceeding.

CustodyItemRgltyCodeVio.description: Represents a junction between a custody item and the related regulatory code violation. The violation can be related to laws, regulations, or code that is associated with the custody item.

CustodyVerfcTypeOverride.description: Represents information about the verification of an entry in the chain of custody.

Custom Object__Feed.description: Represents the feed, specifically posts and feed-tracked changes, on a custom object.

Custom Objects.description: In the user interface, you can extend your org’s data by defining custom objects. Custom objects are custom database tables that allow you to store information unique to your organization. For custom objects, the custom flag—a Boolean field in the describe results—is true.

CustomBrand.description: Represents a custom branding and color scheme.

CustomBrandAsset.description: Represents a branding element in a custom branding scheme. For example, a color, logo image, header image, or footer text.

CustomFieldDisplayValue.description: Stores variation details for the product attribute item view.

CustomHelpMenuItem.description: Represents the items within a section of the Lightning Experience help menu that the admin added to display custom, org-specific help resources.

CustomHelpMenuSection.description: Represents a section of the Lightning Experience help menu that the admin added to display custom, org-specific help resources.

CustomHttpHeader.description: Represents a custom HTTP header that provides context information from Salesforce such as region, org details, or the role of the person viewing the external object.

CustomMsgChannel.description: Represents a custom conversation channel and stores event-driven Messaging settings. Custom conversation channels are implemented for Bring Your Own Channel for Messaging and Bring Your Own Channel for CCaaS Messaging channels.

CustomNotificationType.description: Stores information about custom notification types.

CustomObjectParticipant.description: Represents information about a participant in the context of a custom object record.

CustomPermission.description: Represents a permission created to control access to a custom process or app, such as sending email.

CustomPermissionDependency.description: Represents the dependency between two custom permissions when one custom permission requires that you enable another custom permission.

Customer.description: Represents the customer role of an individual with respect to a particular company or organization.

CustomerProperty.description: Represents the insurable and insured properties of a customer.

DandBCompany.description: Represents a Dun & Bradstreet® company record, which is associated with an account added from Data.com.

Dashboard.description: Represents a dashboard, which shows data from custom reports as visual components. Access is read-only.

Dashboard Event Type.description: Dashboard events contain details about report requests from dashboards. These requests are triggered by dashboard refreshes, subscriptions, and filter changes.

DashboardComponent.description: Represents a dashboard component, which can be a chart, metric, table, or gauge on a dashboard. Access is read-only.

DataAssessmentFieldMetric.description: Represents summary statistics for matched, blank, and differing fields in account records of an org compared to records in Data.com.

DataAssessmentMetric.description: Represents a summary of statistics for fields matched and unmatched in your account records with Data.com account records.

DataAssessmentValueMetric.description: Summarizes the number of fields matched for your account records with Data.com account records.

DataDetPlcyDataSrchExps.description: Represents data search expressions for scanning DataDetect scan policies based on Java regex.

DataDetPlcyMdatScanCrit.description: Represents inclusion and exclusion criteria that filter what DataDetect scan policy object fields are to be scanned based on metadata tags.

DataDetPlcySstvDataCatg.description: Represents the sensitive data categories that the DataDetect scan policy is required to scan.

DataDetectJobObjectSession.description: Represents an object-specific job session that's created whenever a DataDetect scan policy job session runs on a scan policy object.

DataDetectJobSession.description: Represents a run of a DataDetect scan policy that's triggered manually.

DataDetectPolicy.description: Represents a set of parameters that specifies the types of sensitive data to be searched for in a data scan. DataDetect scan policies can also apply filters to a data scan, and select what specific objects and fields are to be scanned.

DataDetectPolicyObjField.description: Represents an object field of the DataDetect scan policy object to be scanned. This object is available in API version 64.0 and later.

DataDetectPolicyObject.description: Represents an object of the DataDetect scan policy to be scanned. This object is available in API version 62.0 and later.

DataDetectPolicySnapshot.description: Represents the snapshot of a DataDetect scan policy and its components retrieved during a job session.

DataDetectScanResult.description: Represents the results of a DataDetect scan policy data scan.

DataEncryptionKey.description: The DataEncryptionKey object is part of the Bring Your Own Key (BYOK) feature, which allows users to upload a data encryption key (DEK) using a public key generated by the Salesforce Shield Key Management Service (KMS). Customers create their own DEKs and upload them to Salesforce. Users access this entity via the API to list DEK keys for auditing purposes. They can also programmatically use this object to create the certificate and to upload key material.

DataIntegrationRecordPurchasePermission.description: Indicates Lightning Data purchase credits that a Salesforce admin has granted to users.

DataKitDeployEvent.description: Represents a data kit deployment event that notifies subscribers of the status of the data kit component deployment. This object is available in API version 61.0 or later.

DataKitDeploymentLog.description: Represents the log details of a data kit component deployment. This object is available in API version 61.0 or later.

DataMaskCustomValueLibrary.description: Represents a set of user-inputted values in a custom library in Data Mask.

DataUseLegalBasis.description: Represents the legal basis for contacting a customer, such as billing or contract.

DataUsePurpose.description: Represents the reason for contacting a prospect or customer, such as for billing, marketing, or surveys

DataWeaveResource.description: Represents the DataWeaveScriptResource class that is generated for all DataWeave scripts.

DatabaseSaveEventLog.description: Database Save events track when records are created,updated, or deleted

DatacloudCompany.description: Represents the fields for Data.com company records.

DatacloudContact.description: The fields and properties for Data.com contact records.

DatacloudDandBCompany.description: Represents a set of read-only fields that are used to return D&B company data from Data.com API calls.

DatacloudOwnedEntity.description: Represents fields in the DatacloudOwnedEntity object. The DatacloudOwnedEntity object tracks user-purchased records.

DatacloudPurchaseUsage.description: Represents an object used to identify and track Data.com record purchases. This object is available in API version 30.0 or later.

DatasetExport.description: Represents a dataset exported from CRM Analytics. When a dataset is exported, the data is converted into a .csv file and the schema is stored in a separate JSON file. These files are stored in two objects: DatasetExport and DatasetExportPart. DatasetExport acts as the header and includes the JSON schema.

DatasetExportPart.description: Represents a dataset exported from CRM Analytics. When a dataset is exported, the data is converted into a .csv file and the schema is stored in a separate JSON file. These files are stored in two objects: DatasetExport and DatasetExportPart. DatasetExportPart contains parts of the .csv file.

DatedConversionRate.description: Represents the dated exchange rates used by an organization for which the multicurrency and the effective dated currency features are enabled.

DealIndirectPartner.description: Represents an indirect partner’s involvement in a deal.

DeclinedEventRelation.description: Represents event participants (invitees or attendees) with the status Declined for a given event.

DeleteEvent.description: Represents a record that has been soft deleted.

DeliveryEstimationSetup.description: Shows the configuration options for the commerce delivery service offered through a web store or sales channel. Includes settings such as delivery location group, channel, fulfillment types, and default fulfillment time.

DeliveryTask.description: Represents information about shipments and orders to be delivered to a store in a visit.

Deviation.description: Represents the information about the deviation from set rules.

DigitalSignature.description: Represents a signature captured on a service report in field service.

DigitalVerification.description: Stores information about the verification of a related record

DigitalWallet.description: Represents a customer’s digital wallet service. Salesforce Payments can use a digital wallet as a payment source when processing payments through a payment gateway.

DirectMessage.description: Represents a direct message conversation between multiple users in Chatter.

Disclosure.description: Represents the disclosure details that a company shares, which can be included by a user in their response document.

DisclosureDefinition.description: Represents information that defines a disclosure type, such as details of the publisher or vendor who created or implemented the report.

DisclosureDefinitionVersion.description: Represents the version information about the disclosure definition.

DisclosureType.description: Represents the types of disclosures that are done by an individual or an organization and the associated metadata.

DisclsReportingPeriod.description: Represents a corporate reporting period that is used for stakeholder disclosure reports.

Dispute.description: Represents the details of a dispute that involves one or multiple disputed transactions.

DisputeItem.description: Represents a transaction that’s being disputed.

DisputeItemArbitration.description: Represents the details of the arbitration or compliance case filed for a transaction that's being disputed.

DisputeItemChargeback.description: Represents the claim and chargeback created by the card issuer for a transaction that's being disputed.

DisputeItemMerchantAlert.description: Represents the alert sent by the card issuer to the merchant. The alert occurs through a chargeback prevention vendor like Ethoca Merchant Alerts™ for a transaction that’s being disputed.

DisputeItemQueueResponse.description: Represents the response received from the job that’s run to fetch the claim details.

DisputeQueueJobRun.description: Represents a job that’s run to fetch the details of the claims.

DisputeReason.description: Represents the reason for the transaction dispute.

DistributorAuthorization.description: Represents the official authorization from an insurance company granting a distributor the permission to act as its agent.

Division.description: A logical segment of your organization's data. For example, if your company is organized into different business units, you could create a division for each business unit, such as “North America,” “Healthcare,” or “Consulting.” Available only if the organization has the Division permission enabled.

DivisionLocalization.description: When the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization, the DivisionLocalization object provides the translation of the label for a division.

DivrsEquityInclSum.description: Represents information that indicates the quantitative view of the organization based on the employee gender, age group, and other fairness indicators.

DocAtchDownloadEventLog.description: Document Attachment Downloads events contain details of document and attachment downloads.

DocChkItemValidatedTarget.description: Represents the details of the document checklist item and the target object against which the document checklist item was validated.

DocClauseSetAsmtQstn.description: Represents a junction between a document clause set and an assessment question.

Document.description: Represents a file that a user has uploaded. Unlike Attachment records, documents are not attached to a parent object.

Document Attachment Downloads Event Type.description: Document Attachment Downloads events contain details of document and attachment downloads.

DocumentAttachmentMap.description: Maps the relationship between an EmailTemplate and its attachment, which is stored as a Document.

DocumentCategory.description: Represents a document category that's used to group the document checklist items.

DocumentCategoryDocumentType.description: Represents a junction between Document Category and Document Type.

DocumentChecklistItem.description: Represents a checklist item for a documentation file upload.

DocumentDecisionRequirement.description: Represents the decision criteria that will be used to determine applicable documents.

DocumentRecipient.description: Connects a Service Report to a Digital Signature.

DocumentType.description: Represents the type of file being uploaded or attached.

Domain.description: Read-only object that represents a custom Web address assigned to a site in your organization.

DomainSite.description: Read-only junction object that joins the Site and Domain objects.

DsarPolicy.description: Represents a Data Subject Access Request (DSAR) policy created in the Privacy Center managed package. DSAR policies anonymize or transfer personal data from your org at your customer’s request. This object is available in API version 50.0 and later.

DsarPolicyLog.description: Represents the history of Data Subject Access Request (DSAR) policy execution requests. This log records the status and results of executed DSAR policies for a customer. This object is available in API version 50.0 and later.

DuplicateJob.description: Represents an instance of a job that identifies duplicates among existing records in the system.

DuplicateJobDefinition.description: Setup object defining a job that identifies duplicate record items globally.

DuplicateJobMatchingRule.description: Represents a MatchingRule to be used with a DuplicateJob sharing the corresponding DuplicateJobMatchingRuleDefinition.

DuplicateJobMatchingRuleDefinition.description: Setup object specifying a MatchingRule to use with DuplicateJob instances that share a DuplicateJobDefinition.

DuplicateRecordItem.description: Represents an individual record that’s part of a duplicate record set. Use this object to create custom report types.

DuplicateRecordSet.description: Represents a group of records that have been identified as duplicates. Each duplicate record set contains one or more duplicate record items. Use this object to create custom report types and view the results of duplicate jobs.

DuplicateRule.description: Represents a duplicate rule for detecting duplicate records.

DynamicDataCapture.description: DynamicDataCapture is a junction object that adds a Form tab to Work Order Overview, and to the related list of a work order, work order line item, or service appointment in the Field Service mobile app.

EconomicPerformanceSum.description: Represents statistics about the direct economic value generated and distributed by an organization or the related income and expenses.

EducInstSearchableProfile.description: Represents information about an educational institution aggregated from other objects for Criteria-Based Search and Filter.

EducInstitutionOffering.description: Represents a junction between an institution's account and other objects, such as program, learning program, and academic term.

EducationalInfoRequest.description: Represents details about a request for information (RFI) raised by prospective students, parents, or counselors.

ElectricityEmssnFctrSet.description: Represents the factors that are used to convert electricity usage into CO₂e, CO₂, CH₄, and N₂O values. This record holds data on the breakdown of sources of electricity by fuel type (grid mixes).

ElectronicMediaGroup.description: Represents the type of media that you can associate with a product or category.

EmailContent.description: Represents a marketing email asset for use with Account Engagement.

EmailDomainFilter.description: Represents a filter that determines whether an email relay is restricted to a specific list of domains.

EmailDomainKey.description: Represents a domain key for an organization’s domain, used to authenticate outbound email that Salesforce sends on the organization’s behalf.

EmailInsight.description: Represents an insight generated from an email interaction. EmailInsights acts as a central place to store various types of insights related to email messages. The insights stored include status, type, and time of generation. Only certain types of insights can be created based on a pre-configured list of insight types.

EmailInsightAction.description: Represents the actions that have been taken, or could be taken, in relation to email insights. It logs different types of actions and associated metadata, helping to track and manage the activities and decisions made based on email insights.

EmailMessageRelation.description: Represents the relationship between an email and contacts, leads, and users.

EmailRelay.description: Represents the configuration for sending an email relay. An email relay routes email sent from Salesforce through your company’s email servers.

EmailRoutingAddress.description: An email address used for Email-to-Case. Email routing addresses store a unique email services address provided by Salesforce and configuration options for emails received by this address.

EmailStatus.description: Represents the status of email sent.

EmailTemplate.description: Represents a template for an email, mass email, list email, or Sales Engagement email. Supported in first-generation managed packages only.

EmailTemplateMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for an email template.

EmbeddedServiceDetail.description: Represents a metadata catalog object that exposes fields from the underlying Embedded Service setup objects defined in each EmbeddedServiceConfig deployment for guest users. Guest users don’t have direct access to the Embedded Service setup objects.

EmbeddedServiceLabel.description: Represents a customized label in Embedded Chat or embedded Appointment Management.

EmissionsActivity.description: Represents a company’s emission generating activities and the greenhouse gas categories that are used to aggregate emissions for these activities.

EmissionsAllocation.description: Represents information about the emissions from a child or partner account that are allocated to an account.

EmissionsForecastFact.description: Represents information about the time periods, measures, and dimensions used to forecast the emissions of a company. The emissions forecast of the company is generated based on its business measures such as revenue or employee count, and the actual emissions data from previous years.

EmpBenefitSummary.description: Represents statistics about benefits provided to employees and the usage of benefits.

EmpUserProvisionProcessErr.description: Represents an employee-user provisioning process error.

Employee.description: Represents an employee within a company or organization.

Employee2.description: Represents an employee within a company or an organization.

EmployeeCrisisAssessment.description: Represents a crisis assessment of an Employee.

EmployeeDemographicSum.description: Represents statistics about employees based on their demographic information, such as employee count by age group, by gender, and by region.

EmployeeDevelopmentSum.description: Represents statistics about training and development provided to upskill the employees.

Employment.description: Represents the details of an individual's employment with an organization.

EmploymentCompensationSummary.description: Represents information about stakeholder engagement to assess the importance of environmental, social, and governance (ESG) issues for them.

EmploymentOffer.description: Represents an employment offer for a selected candidate.

EmploymentOfferVettingEval.description: Represents a junction between an employment offer and a vetting evaluation of the offer recipient.

EmssnRdctnCommitment.description: Represents information about a company's commitment to reducing its carbon emissions. This commitment is in line with the Paris Agreement’s goal to achieve a low-carbon future. For example, companies sign the Business Ambition for 1.5°C commitment letter and commit to set emission reduction targets to limit temperature rise to 1.5°C above pre-industrial levels.

EmssnReductionTarget.description: Represents information about the science-based or non-science-based target set by a company to fulfill its emissions reduction commitment. This target indicates the company’s emissions reduction goal. A company’s emissions reduction goal could be to reduce carbon emissions or increase renewable energy for reaching a target metric tonnes of CO2e (tCO2e) within a specific timeframe.

EnablementMeasureDefinition.description: Represents an Enablement measure, which specifies the job-related activity that a user performs to complete a milestone or outcome in an Enablement program. A measure identifies a source object and optional related objects, with optional field filters and filter logic, for tracking the activity. This object also represents Enablement measure information in Metadata API.

EnablementProgram.description: Represents an Enablement program, which includes exercises and measurable milestones to help users such as sales reps achieve specific outcomes related to your company’s revenue goals.

EnablementProgramDefinition.description: Represents Enablement program information in Metadata API.

EnblMeasureObjectDefinition.description: Represents the criteria for an object that tracks the job-related activity for an Enablement measure in an Enablement program. A separate EnblMeasureObjectDefinition is used for a measure's source object and each optional related object.

EnblPgmTaskMeasureProgress.description: Represents a user’s progress through the object and field requirements that an Enablement measure defines for an outcome or milestone in an Enablement program.

EnblProgramSection.description: Represents an optional section in an Enablement program. A section can include other program items, such as milestones and exercises.

EnblProgramTaskDefinition.description: Represents an outcome, a milestone, or an exercise in an Enablement program. A program task is also known as a program item.

EnblProgramTaskMeasure.description: Represents the connection between an Enablement measure and a specific milestone or outcome in an Enablement program.

EnblProgramTaskProgress.description: Represents a user’s progress towards completing an outcome, a milestone, or an exercise in an Enablement program.

EnblProgramTaskSubCategory.description: Represents a custom exercise type that an Enablement admin adds to an Enablement program in Program Builder. A custom exercise type also requires a corresponding EnblProgramTaskDefinition record for Program Builder and corresponding LearningItem and LearningItemType records for when users take the exercise in the Guidance Center.

EnergyAttrCertCredit.description: Represents information about the energy attribute certificate credits related to energy attribute certificate purchase.

EnergyAttrCertPurchase.description: Represents information about the purchase of energy attribute certificates from the clean energy project supplier. The information includes terms of engagement and the delivery type of energy attribute certificate.

EnergyAttrCreditDstr.description: Represents a junction between energy attribute credits and stationary asset energy use indicating the quantity of credits distributed for a specific energy use.

EnergyServiceAgreement.description: The services or commodities purchased by a customer, for a specified product and optionally linked to a Contract. Contracted Services can be physical goods (eg. appliances), commodity services (eg. electricity, gas or water) or other miscellaneous services (eg. homeowner insurance, boiler maintenance contract).

EnergyServiceAgreementItem.description: Represents the details of the Energy Service Agreement object such as the time, location, and pricing information.

EngagementAttendee.description: Represents information about an attendee of an engagement. For example, when a customer initiates an engagement interaction by calling a service representative to inquire about an insurance claim, this object stores information about the customer and the service representative.

EngagementChannelType.description: Represents a channel through which a customer can be reached for communication. The Engagement Channel Type object supports only the English language.

EngagementChannelWorkType.description: Represents the relationship between an Engagement Channel Type object and a Work Type object for Salesforce Scheduler.

EngagementInteraction.description: Represents information about an interaction between a service representative or any other specialist in an organization and the organization’s customer. Engagement interactions can be initiated through communication channels and can cover one or more topics. For example, a customer can initiate an engagement interaction by calling a service representative to inquire about an insurance claim.

EngagementTopic.description: Represents information about the topics discussed by a customer and other attendees during an engagement. For example, when a customer initiates an engagement interaction by calling a service representative to inquire about an insurance claim, the topic of the engagement is Claim.

EnhancedLetterhead.description: Represents an enhanced letterhead that can be associated with a Lightning email template that doesn’t use the Salesforce Merge Language (SML).

EnrollmentEligibilityCriteria.description: Represents criteria that define patient enrollment eligibility for one or more care programs.

Entitlement.description: Represents the customer support an account or contact is eligible to receive.

EntitlementContact.description: Represents a Contact eligible to receive customer support via an Entitlement.

EntitlementTemplate.description: Represents predefined terms of customer support for a product (Product2).

EntityHistory.description: Represents historical information about an object’s changed field values.

EntityMilestone.description: Represents a required step in a customer support process on a work order. The Salesforce user interface uses the term “object milestone.

EntitySubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a record or another user.

EnvironmentHubMember.description: Represents a member organization in the Environment Hub.

EnvironmentalRisk.description: Represents information about the risk that the environmental resources create for an organization.

Event.description: Represents an event in the calendar. In the user interface, event and task records are collectively referred to as activities.

EventBusSubscriber.description: Represents a trigger, process, or flow that’s subscribed to a platform event or a change data capture event. Doesn’t include CometD or Pub/Sub API subscribers.

EventRelation.description: Represents a person (a user, lead, or contact) or a resource (such as a conference room) invited to an event. This object lets you add or remove invitees from an event and use the API to manage invitees’ responses to invitations. If Shared Activities is enabled, EventRelation can also represent other objects that are related to an event. EventRelation does not support triggers, workflow, or data validation rules.

EventRelayConfig.description: Represents the configuration of an event relay, which relays platform events and change data capture events from Salesforce to Amazon EventBridge.

EventRelayFeedback.description: Represents execution state information about an event relay from Salesforce to Amazon EventBridge for platform events and change data capture events. Query this object to get information such as the event relay status and any error message.

EventTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with an Event.

EventWhoRelation.description: Represents the relationship between an event and a lead or contacts. This derived object is a filtered version of the EventRelation object; that is, IsParent is true and IsWhat is false. It doesn’t represent relationships to invitees or to accounts, opportunities, or other objects.

Examination.description: Represents information about the authorized examinations that qualify a license or permit.

Expense.description: Represents an expense linked to a work order. Service resource technicians can log expenses, such as tools or travel costs.

ExpenseReport.description: Represents a report that summarizes expenses.

ExpenseReportEntry.description: Represents an entry in an expense report.

ExplainabilityMsgTemplateLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of the message in an explainability message template for an expression set step element.

ExpressionFilter.description: Represents a logical expression that’s used to control the execution of macro instructions.

ExpressionFilterCriteria.description: Represents a condition in an expression that’s used to control the execution of macro instructions.

ExpressionSet.description: Represents information about an expression set. An expression set performs a series of calculations using lookups and user-defined variables and constants.

ExpressionSetConstraintObj.description: Represents the association between a Product object and the constraint model tags defined in a given constraint model.

ExpressionSetDefinitionContextDefinition.description: Represents a relationship between an expression set definition and a context definition. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.

ExpressionSetVersion.description: Represents information about a specific version of an expression set. This object is also accessible through the UI API, which enables its use in components like Lightning Web Components (LWC).

ExpressionSetView.description: Represents a virtual object that provides a consolidated view of file-based expression set. File-based expression sets are read-only templates. To be able to modify file-based expression sets, you must clone them first.

ExpsSetObjectAliasFieldVw.description: Represents the virtual object that provides a consolidated view of source object and its alias, and the source object fields and their aliases that are used in an expression set. This object is used to check the permission level required to access the underlying object fields associated with their field aliases.

ExtDataShare.description: Represents a data share, which is a collection of Data Cloud objects that can be shared with other Data Cloud orgs or third-party partners.

ExtKnowledgeConnector.description: Represents a connector to a third-party knowledge source for Unified Knowledge.

External Cross-Org Callout Event Type.description: External Cross-Org Callout events represent external data callouts via the cross-org adapter for Salesforce Connect.

External Custom Apex Callout Event Type.file: objects/E/External Custom Apex Callout Event Type.json
External Custom Apex Callout Event Type.description: External Custom Apex Callout events represent external data callouts via custom adapters for Salesforce Connect.

External Data Source Callout Event Type.file: objects/E/External Data Source Callout Event Type.json
External Data Source Callout Event Type.description: External Data Source Callout events represent external data callouts via the Salesforce Connect adapters for Amazon DynamoDB and Amazon Athena.

External OData Callout Event Type.description: External OData Callout events represent external data callouts via the OData 2.0 and OData 4.0 adapters for Salesforce Connect.

ExternalAccountHierarchy.description: Represents the external account hierarchy, which works like a role-based hierarchy. Use ExternalAccountHierarchy to allow partner and customer users to share data with other external accounts in their hierarchy.

ExternalAccountHierarchyHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to values in the fields of an external account hierarchy.

ExternalDataSource.description: Represents an external data source, which defines connection details for integration with data and content that are stored outside the Salesforce org.

ExternalDataUserAuth.description: Stores authentication settings for a Salesforce user to access an external system. The external system must be defined in an external data source or a named credential that’s configured to use per-user authentication.

ExternalEncryptionRootKey.description: Represents metadata about root keys stored in third-party key stores that are used to generate and secure keys that encrypt Salesforce data.

ExternalEvent.description: Holds native iOS or Android calendar event details for the Salesforce Today feature in the Salesforce mobile app.

ExternalEventMapping.description: Holds native iOS or Android calendar event details for the Salesforce Today feature in the Salesforce mobile app.

ExternalLearning.description: Represents information that defines a training that is made available by an external provider as a course, program, or on-site experience, for a contact.

ExternalLearningPtcpResult.description: Represents the outcome of a student's participation in an external learning.

ExternalSocialAccount.description: Represents a managed social media account on a social network such as Facebook or Twitter.

ExtlPtcpRsltLrnrPgmRqmt.description: Represents a junction between the External Learning Participant Result and Learner Program Requirement objects.

ExtlRecShrCnct.description: Represents authentication data to make outbound calls to and inbound calls from an external system to publish events for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrCnctAccnt.description: Represents an association between an account and an external record share connection for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrField.description: Represents an imported, exported, or updated external record share field for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrFieldMap.description: Represents the external record share field mapping between the sender and receiver for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrLead.description: Represents the Lead record of a vendor org if you’re a partner. If you’re a vendor for Partner Connect, this object represents a partner org.

ExtlRecShrObject.description: Represents a shared object for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrOpportunity.description: Represents the opportunity for Partner Connect in the vendor org if you’re a partner and the partner org if you’re the vendor.

ExtlRecShrPcklstOptn.description: Represents a picklist option of an external record share picklist field shared between a partner and vendor for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrPicklistMap.description: Represents the external record share picklist field mapping between the partner and vendor system for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrRecordMap.description: Represents the lead or opportunity being mapped between a partner and vendor for Partner Connect.

FSL__Time_Dependency__c.description: Represents a dependency between two service appointments. This object is used to define scheduling relationships between two appointments. It allows you to determine the order and timing in which dependent appointments should be scheduled.

FeeScheduleDefinition.description: Stores fee schedule information for contracts of Standard Care Fee Agreement types.

FeedAttachment.description: Represents an attachment to a feed item, such as a file attachment or a link. Use FeedAttachment to add various attachments to one feed item.

FeedComment.description: Represents a comment added to a feed by a user.

FeedItem.description: FeedItem represents an entry in the feed, such as changes in a record feed, including text posts, link posts, and content posts.

FeedLike.description: Indicates that a user has liked a feed item.

FeedPollChoice.description: Shows the choices for a poll posted in the feed.

FeedPollVote.description: Shows how users voted on a poll posted in the feed.

FeedPost.description: FeedPost represents the following types of changes in a record feed, such as AccountFeed: text posts, link posts, and content posts.

FeedRevision.description: Holds the revision history of a specific feed item or comment, including a list of attributes that changed for each revision.

FeedTrackedChange.description: Represents an individual field change or set of field changes. A FeedTrackedChange is a child object of a record feed, such as AccountFeed.

FieldChangeSnapshot.description: Use this virtual object to learn which opportunities' close dates changed during the specified time period.

FieldHistoryArchive.description: Represents field history values for all objects that retain field history. FieldHistoryArchive is a big object, available only to users with the “Retain Field History” permission.

FieldPermissions.description: Represents the enabled field permissions for the parent PermissionSet.

FieldSecurityClassification.description: Represents a field’s data sensitivity value selected from the SecurityClassification picklist.

FieldServiceMobileSettings.description: Represents a configuration of settings that control the Field Service iOS and Android mobile app experience.

FieldServiceOrgSettings.description: Represents the org settings for Field Service, such as Appointment Assistant settings.

FileSearchActivity.description: Represents search activity on a file.

FinAssetPortfolioTgtAlloc.description: Stores target asset allocation for a financial account, person account, or household.

FinServ AccountContactRelation Custom Fi.description: Represents the relationship between an individual (specifically the contact part of the individual) and the household (account) that the individual is a member of. AccountContactRelation is a standard object that is available through the Shared Contacts feature. Custom fields extend the AccountContactRelation standard object for use in Financial Services Cloud.

FinServ AuthorizationForm Custom Fields.description: Represents the specific version and effective dates of a form that is associated with consent, such as a privacy policy or terms and conditions.

FinServ AuthorizationFormConsent Custom.description: Represents the date and way in which a user consented to an authorization form.

FinServ AuthorizationFormText Custom Fie.description: Represents an authorization form’s text and language settings.

FinServ_AccountAccountRelation__c.description: Represents a relationship between two accounts, such as between a household and a business account.

FinServ_Alert__c.description: Represents notifications to alert advisors about their client accounts.

FinServ_AssetsAndLiabilities__c.description: Represents assets or liabilities that are not represented in a client's financial accounts, such as real estate or collectibles.

FinServ_BillingStatement__c.description: Represents a billing statement for an individual’s financial account.

FinServ_Card__c.description: Represents credit or debit card associated with this financial account.

FinServ_ChargesAndFees__c.description: Represents agreed-to fees and charges for servicing an individual’s financial account.

FinServ_ContactContactRelation__c.description: Represents the relationship between any two individuals.

FinServ_Employment__c.description: Represents information about an individual’s employment history.

FinServ_FinancialAccountRole__c.description: Represents the role occupied by a person or organizational entity that is involved with a financial account, such as a beneficiary or trustee.

FinServ_FinancialAccountTransaction__c.description: Represents information about a single financial account transaction.

FinServ_FinancialAccount__c.description: Represents a financial account such as an investment account, bank account, or insurance policy.

FinServ_FinancialGoal__c.description: This Financial Goal object is installed in your Financial Services Cloud Salesforce org when you install the Financial Services Cloud Managed Package. It represents a client’s financial goal, such as college funds or a major purchase.

FinServ_FinancialHolding__c.description: Represents a financial holding in an investment account, such as shares of stock.

FinServ_IdentificationDocument__c.description: Represents information about documents used to verify an individual’s identity.

FinServ_LifeEvent__c.description: Represents a client’s life event, such as a birth or marriage.

FinServ_PolicyPaymentMethod__c.description: Represents the premium payment method for a policy, such as credit card, debit card, or internet banking.

FinServ_ReciprocalRole__c.description: Represents the other entity’s corresponding role in a one-to-one relationship between entities.

FinServ_Revenue__c.description: Represents data from Financial Services Cloud and external systems to aggregate revenue streams for an advisor’s book of business.

FinServ_Securities__c.description: Represents a security, such as a stock or bond.

FinancialAccount.description: Represents a financing option, such as an automotive loan or lease related to a customer.

FinancialAccountAddress.description: Represents an address related to a financial account.

FinancialAccountBalance.description: Represents the details about a financial account balance.

FinancialAccountFee.description: Represents the charges levied on a financial account

FinancialAccountMilestone.description: Represents the events in the lifecycle of a financial account.

FinancialAccountParty.description: Represents the relationship between an account or a contact and a financial account.

FinancialAccountStatement.description: Represents a periodic statement summary for a financial account.

FinancialAccountTransaction.description: Represents a single transaction related to a loan or a lease.

FinancialDeal.description: Represents the deal that the financial institution is working on.

FinancialDealAsset.description: Represents the assets included in the financial deal.

FinancialDealBid.description: Represents the bids placed by financial deal parties in the financial deal.

FinancialDealInteraction.description: Represents a junction between an interaction and a financial deal.

FinancialDealParticipant.description: Represents the user or the group with whom the deal is shared.

FinancialDealParty.description: Represents the parties, such as partners and competitors, that are involved in the deal.

FinancialDealProduct.description: Represents the products (services) offered by the bank in the deal.

FinancialGoal.description: This Financial Goal object is a standard Salesforce object. It represents a financial goal for a person account.

FinancialGoalFunding.description: The financial goal of an individual or person account that requires funding.

FinancialGoalParty.description: Represents a junction between the financial goal and the person account.

FinancialPlan.description: Represents a financial plan for a person account.

FinclAcctPtyFinclAsset.description: Represents the financial account associated with the financial asset for a specific account or contact.

FinclDealInteractionSummary.description: Represents a junction between an interaction summary and a financial deal.

FiscalYearSettings.description: Settings to define a custom or standard fiscal year for your organization. This object has a parent-child relationship with the Period object.

FldSvcObjChg.description: Represents a change made to one of a service appointment’s tracked fields.

FldSvcObjChgDtl.description: Represents the details of a change made to one of a service appointment’s tracked fields.

Fleet.description: Represents a group of assets used in commercial, service, or transport operations in the manufacturing industry.

FleetAsset.description: Represents the relationship between an asset and the fleet to which it belongs.

FleetParticipant.description: Represents the relationship between a fleet and a participant, such as an account, a contact, or a user.

FlexQueueItem.description: Represents an asynchronous Apex job in the Apex flex queue. Provides information about the job type and flex queue position of the AsyncApexJob.

FlowDefinitionView.description: Represents the description of a flow definition.

FlowInterview.description: Represents a flow interview. A flow interview is a running instance of a flow. This object is available in API version 32.0 and later.

FlowInterviewLog.description: Represents the logs of a screen flow interview. An interview is an instance of a running or previously run flow.

FlowInterviewLogEntry.description: Represents the log of a specific element that’s executed by a screen flow interview. An interview is an instance of a running or previously run flow.

FlowInterviewLogOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a FlowInterviewLog with users other than the owner.

FlowInterviewOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a FlowInterview with users other than the owner.

FlowInterviewShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a FlowInterview.

FlowNavMetricEventLog.description: Flow Navigation Metric event logs contain metric data for flow interviews such as total execution time, number of interviews, and number of errors.

FlowOrchestration.description: Represents the details of an orchestration definition.

FlowOrchestrationInstRelaObj.description: Represents a junction between a flow orchestration instance and a related object.

FlowOrchestrationInstance.description: Represents a run-time instance of an orchestration.

FlowOrchestrationLog.description: Represents logging data for a FlowOrchestrationInstance.

FlowOrchestrationStageInstance.description: Represents a run-time instance of a stage in a run-time instance of an orchestration.

FlowOrchestrationStepInstance.description: Represents a run-time instance of a step in a run-time instance of a stage of a run-time instance of an orchestration.

FlowOrchestrationVersion.description: Represents the version of an orchestration.

FlowOrchestrationWorkItem.description: Represents a work item associated with a run-time instance of an interactive step in a run-time instance of an orchestration.

FlowRecord.description: Represents the details of a flow. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.

FlowRecordElement.description: Represents a single element within a flow version. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.

FlowRecordElementOccurrence.description: Represents the execution metrics for a single element within a flow version.

FlowRecordRelation.description: Represents a relationship between a record and a flow interview. When a flow interview is paused, Salesforce uses the $Flow.CurrentRecord global variable in the flow to associate the interview with a record.

FlowRecordVersion.description: Represents the version of a flow. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.

FlowRecordVersionOccurrence.description: Represents an instance of a recurring flow that runs on a schedule.

FlowStageRelation.description: Represents a relationship between a paused flow interview and its stages. When a flow interview is paused, Salesforce creates a FlowStageRelation record for each stage that’s set to the $Flow.CurrentStage or $Flow.ActiveStages global variable.

FlowTestResult.description: Represents the results for a flow test associated with a flow version.

FlowTestView.description: Represents the description of a flow test associated with a flow definition.

FlowVariableView.description: Represents a variable within the flow version.

FlowVersionView.description: Represents the version of a flow definition.

Folder.description: Represents a repository for a Dashboard, Document, EmailTemplate, Macro, QuickText, or Report. Only one type of item can be contained in a folder.

FolderedContentDocument.description: Represents the relationship between a parent and child ContentFolderItem in a ContentWorkspace.

ForecastingAdjustment.description: This object represents an individual forecast manager’s adjustment for a subordinate’s or child territory’s forecast via a ForecastingItem.

ForecastingColumnDefinitionLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a custom calculated column or custom reference data column label when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization.

ForecastingCustomCategory.description: Represents a custom forecasting category used for forecast rollups.

ForecastingCustomData.description: Represents forecast data from external sources to display in the forecasts page. For example, risk or last year’s revenue.

ForecastingDisplayedFamily.description: Represents the table in Forecasts Settings where an admin selects the product families that users can forecast on in Lightning Experience.

ForecastingFact.description: This object is read-only and links a ForecastingItem with its opportunities, such as opportunities that share the same owner or forecast category and have a closing date within the period of the forecasting item.

ForecastingFilter.description: Represents the custom filter for including or excluding data from opportunity forecasts.
