ForecastingFilterCondition.description: Represents the custom filter condition logic for including or excluding data from opportunity forecasts.

ForecastingGroup.description: Represents groups used to roll up forecast totals on the forecasts page.

ForecastingGroupItem.description: Represents the value within the picklist that is specified as the forecasting group for a forecast type. For example, if you have a forecasting group that identifies the industry an opportunity is part of, this object represents the value in the the industry picklist that’s chosen to be part of the group.

ForecastingItem.description: This object is read-only used for individual forecast amounts. Users see amounts based on their perspectives and forecast roles.

ForecastingOwnerAdjustment.description: This object represents an individual forecast user’s adjustment of their own forecast, including territory forecasts they own, via a ForecastingItem.

ForecastingQuota.description: This object represents an individual user’s or territory’s quota for a specified time period.

ForecastingShare.description: Represents forecasts shared between a forecast manager and a user.

ForecastingSourceDefinition.description: Represents the object, measure, date type, and hierarchy that a forecast uses to project sales.

ForecastingSrcRecJudgment.description: Represents forecast managers’ judgment of whether they consider an opportunity-related deal to be certain to close.

ForecastingSubmissionItem.description: Represents the values for each forecast category in a submitted forecast.

ForecastingType.description: Used to identify the forecast type associated with ForecastingAdjustment, ForecastingOwnerAdjustment, ForecastingQuota, ForecastingFact, and ForecastingItem objects.

ForecastingTypeSource.description: Maps a forecasting source definition to a forecast type.

ForecastingUserPreference.description: Represents the forecasting selections that a user has made, such as display options, date range, forecasting type, and currency.

FormulaFunction.description: Represents a function used when building a formula, including examples and uses.

FormulaFunctionAllowedType.description: Represents the functions that are supported in the given formula context.

FormulaFunctionCategory.description: Represents the category to which a formula belongs when building a formula.

FrcstCustmCatgRampRateSrc.description: Represents the total contract value used for custom bulk adjustments.

FrcstCustmzAdjustment.description: Represents an individual forecast manager’s adjustment of a subordinate’s consumption forecast.

FrcstCustmzOwnerAdjustment.description: Represents an individual forecast user’s adjustment of their own consumption forecast.

Frequently Occurring Fields.description: In addition to system fields, these fields are found on many objects.

FrgtHaulingEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 freight hauling.

FrgtHaulingEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to freight hauling.

FuelType.description: Represents information about the additional fuel types defined by a customer.

FuelTypeSustnUom.description: Represents a mapping between the additional fuel types and their corresponding unit of measure values defined by a customer.

FulfillmentOrder.description: Represents a group of products, fees, and delivery charges on a single order that share the same fulfillment location, delivery method, and recipient. The FulfillmentOrderLineItems belonging to a FulfillmentOrder are associated with OrderItemSummary objects belonging to a single OrderSummary.

FulfillmentOrderItemAdjustment.description: Represents a price adjustment on a FulfillmentOrderLineItem. Corresponds to an OrderItemAdjustmentLineSummary associated with the corresponding OrderItemSummary.

FulfillmentOrderItemTax.description: Represents the tax on a FulfillmentOrderLineItem or FulfillmentOrderItemAdjustment. Corresponds to an OrderItemTaxLineItemSummary.

FulfillmentOrderLineItem.description: Represents a product or delivery charge belonging to a FulfillmentOrder. Corresponds to an OrderItemSummary.

FunctionConnection.description: Represents a connection between an org and Salesforce Functions.

FunctionInvocationRequest.description: Represents invocation information for a Salesforce Function.

FunctionReference.description: Represents a deployed Salesforce Function associated with an org.

FundingAward.description: Represents an award given to an individual or organization to facilitate a goal related to the funder’s mission.

FundingAwardAmendment.description: Represents a modification to the scope or finances of a previously approved award.

FundingAwardParticipant.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a funding award.

FundingAwardRequirement.description: Represents a deliverable or milestone that is needed for the award to either be approved or closed.

FundingAwardRqmtSection.description: Represents a part of a funding award requirement to be completed or reviewed.

FundingDisbursement.description: Represents a payment that has been made or scheduled to be made to a funding recipient.

FundingOppParticipant.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a funding opportunity.

FundingOpportunity.description: The pool of money available for distribution for a specific purpose.

GameDefinition.description: Represents information about a game that the loyalty program offers to its members.

GameParticipant.description: Represents a junction between a game definition and a participant who is either an account, a contact, or a loyalty program member.

GameParticipantReward.description: Represents the reward that’s provided to a participant after they’ve played a game.

GameReward.description: The reward that’s offered to participants of a game.

GenAIConversationSummary.description: Represents a generated summary of a voice or video call.

GenAiPlannerDefinition.description: Represents an agent planner service that uses a large language model (LLM) and a reasoning strategy to decompose a given task into smaller subtasks, identify the most suitable actions for each subtask, and invoke them.

GenAiPlannerFunctionDef.description: Represents a relationship between the agent planner service and agent actions.

GenAiPluginDefinition.description: Represents an agent topic, which is a category of actions related to a particular job to be done by AI agents.

GeneratedWaste.description: Represents the information on the waste generated in operations, the waste generated while treating end-of-life products that were sold, and so on.

GenericVisitTask.description: Represents information about a task that can be performed during a visit.

GenericVisitTaskContext.description: Represents the context or purpose for a generic visit task.

GeolocationBasedAction.description: Represents a geolocation-based action, which is an action that’s triggered when a user enters, exits, or is within the area of the associated object.

GiftCommitmentSchedule.description: Represents the schedule for fulfilling the commitment.

GnrcVstKeyPerformanceInd.description: Represents the key performance indicators that can be recorded while performing a task during a visit. You can compare the expected and actual metric values with the key performance indicator records.

GnrcVstTaskContextRelation.description: Represents common attributes used for a visit task and a visit task context.

Goal.description: The Goal object represents the components of a goal such as its name, description, and status.

GoalAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a goal.

GoalAssignmentDetail.description: Represents additional information associated with a GoalAssignment record.

GoalDefinition.description: The definition of a care plan goal in the reusable PGI library that’s a part of Integrated Care Management. When instantiated, GoalDefinition records create GoalAssignment records that serve as goals in care plans.

GoalLink.description: Represents the relationship between two goals. This is a many-to-many relationship, meaning that each goal can link to many other goals.

GoogleDoc.description: Represents a link to a Google Document.

GovtFinancialAsstSum.description: Represents information about the financial assistance received from governments.

GroundTravelEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 ground travel.

GroundTravelEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to ground travel.

GroupCensus.description: Represents a snapshot of statistics about eligible members (employees or members) of a group (employer or association) and their legal dependents. Use this entity in quoting, rating, and the subsequent enrollment process. Child object of employer or group Account.

GroupCensusMember.description: Represents personal information about a member, for example employee or association member, or their dependents. GroupCensusMember is used to estimate the insurance plan cost for the group. This object is also used in the enrollment process to retrieve the member and dependent details. Child object of GroupCensus.

GroupCensusMemberPlan.description: Represents the association of GroupCensusMember and ContractGroupPlan. Use this entity when census data includes previous member enrollment plan details and new member plan details. You can populate GroupCensusMemberPlan by reading the enrollment census in the enrollment services before creating insurance policies.

GroupClass.description: Represents the classification of group members that receive similar benefits. Example classes include executives, union, and office workers. Child object of employer or group Account.

GroupClassContribution.description: Represents employer or group contributions for GroupClass members and their dependents on a per product category such as medical, dental, or vision. Child object of GroupClass.

GroupMember.description: Represents a User or Group that is a member of a public group.

GroupMembershipEventLog.description: Group Membership events capture details about changes to public group and queue membership, such as when members are added to or removed from the public group or queue.

GtwyProvPaymentMethodType.description: The gateway provider payment method type allows integrators and payment providers to choose an active payment to receive an order's payment data rather than allowing the Salesforce Order Management platform to select a default payment method.

GuestBuyerProfile.description: Represents a store's guest buyer profile, which allows unauthenticated buyers to browse the store.

HealthCareDiagnosis.description: Represents information related to industry-standard healthcare diagnosis codes. Before the Spring ’21 release, the Healthcare Procedure and Healthcare Diagnosis objects stored codes specifically related to procedures and diagnoses. These codes were used for prior-authorization requests and approval processes. Since the Spring’21 release, Health Cloud uses the Code Set and Code Set Bundle objects for this purpose instead.

HealthCareProcedure.description: Represents information related to industry-standard healthcare procedure codes. Before the Spring ’21 release, the Healthcare Procedure and Healthcare Diagnosis objects stored codes specifically related to procedures and diagnoses. These codes were used for prior-authorization requests and approval processes. Since the Spring’21 release, Health Cloud uses the Code Set and Code Set Bundle objects for this purpose instead.

HealthScore.description: Represents a subject’s score for a specific score category.

HealthScoreActionLog.description: Represents the log of actions triggered from the Dynamic Actions for Unified Health Scoring component in the Unified Health Scoring feature.

HealthcareFacilityNetwork.description: Represents a junction object identifying the insurance network that a location or business entity is a part of. Network participation records are also stored in this object.

HealthcarePayerNetwork.description: Represents an insurance network group. For example, an insurance company’s exclusive provider organization (EPO) plans.

HealthcarePractitionerFacility.description: Represents the different locations in which a practitioner provides services.

HealthcareProvider.description: Represents business-level details about the healthcare organization or the practitioner.

HealthcareProviderNpi.description: Represents identifiers from the National Provider Identifier that are assigned to every facility and licensed practitioner in the United States. Also includes NPI assigned date, primary mailing address on file, and so on.

HealthcareProviderService.description: Represents a junction object between a HealthcareService and a HealthcareProvider or HealthcareFacility or HealthcarePractitionerFacility.

HealthcareProviderSpecialty.description: Represents specialties for a practitioner or a service provider organization. A provider can have multiple specialties such as anesthesiology and cardiovascular.

HealthcareProviderTaxonomy.description: Represents the taxonomy or subspecialty codes for a provider or facility. A provider or facility can have multiple taxonomies.

HealthcareServiceDetail.description: Represents a junction object between a CareService and a CodeSetBundle.

HierCondHlthCodeMapping.description: Represents how Hierarchical Condition Category (HCC) codes map to condition codes for a specific year.

HierCondHlthRskAdjFctr.description: Stores the risk adjustment factor for patients and members based on the set of Hierarchical Condition Category (HCC) codes that apply to them and the status of their benefits eligibility.

HlthCareProvTreatedCondition.description: Represents a junction object between a healthcare provider, facility, or practitioner and a problem definition that's related to a health condition, such as disease or illness.

Holiday.description: Represents the fields in the Holiday object that are used by Salesforce Scheduler. A holiday is a period during which your service resource is unavailable for appointment scheduling.

HotelStayEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 hotel stay.

HotelStayEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to hotel stay.

IconDefinition.description: Represents the icon-related metadata for a custom tab.

Idea.description: Represents an idea on which users are allowed to comment and vote, for example, a suggestion for an enhancement to an existing product or process.

IdeaComment.description: Represents a comment that a user has submitted in response to an idea.

IdeaReputation.description: Represents a collection of statistics and scores derived from a user’s activity within an Ideas zone or internal organization.

IdeaReputationLevel.description: Represents a reputation level within an Ideas zone or internal organization and is used by the system to calculate reputation. You can create up to 25 levels per zone or internal organization.

IdeaTheme.description: Represents an invitation to zone members to submit ideas that are focused on a specific topic.

IdentityDocument.description: Represents information about documents used to identify Financial Services Cloud clients.

IdentityVerificationProcDef.description: Represents the definition of the identity verification process. Available in API version 54.0 and later.

IdentityVerificationProcDtl.description: Used to configure the search function as well as the minimum number of verifiers for the identity verification process. Available in API version 54.0 and later.

IdentityVerificationProcFld.description: Used to configure the questions or criteria for verifying the identity of a caller. Available in API version 54.0 and later.

IdpEventLog.description: Represents the Identity Provider Event Log. This log records both problems and successes with inbound SAML or OpenID Connect authentication requests from another app provider. It also records outbound SAML responses when Salesforce is acting as an identity provider.

IframeWhiteListUrl.description: Represents a list of trusted external domains that you allow to frame your Embedded Service, Surveys, and Visualforce pages.

Image.description: Represents the details of an image.

ImpactRiskOpportunity.description: Represents an impact, risk, or opportunity that can be evaluated and scored as a part of an organization's double-materiality assessment. Also known as an IRO.

ImpactRiskOpportunityScore.description: Represents the score of an impact, risk, or opportunity for an assessment.

ImpactRiskOpportunityTopic.description: Represents a junction between an impact risk opportunity and a materiality topic.

ImpcRiskOppAssessment.description: Represents an assessment of ESG-related impacts, risks, and opportunities for an organization.

ImpcRiskOppAssessmentTopic.description: Represents a junction between an impact risk opportunity assessment and a materiality topic.

InStoreLocation.description: Create locations within a retail store’s layout such as aisles, shelves, or backrooms.

Incident.description: An Incident is any unplanned business interruption that has wide-sweeping impacts and requires an urgent fix. This object contains the details of the incident, documenting the history of the incident from registration to closure.

IncidentRelatedItem.description: Represents a junction object that relates an Incident to an Asset or Product.

IndexRate.description: Represents a base rate that’s defined by an authority.

IndicatorAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of an indicator definition that's used to measure the performance of an outcome or a related activity.

IndicatorDefinition.description: Represents information about the indicator assignment and the process of measuring and calculating the indicator results.

IndicatorPerformancePeriod.description: Represents information about a specified time period including the frequency at which indicator results should be calculated and the baseline value of the indicator.

IndicatorResult.description: Represents the result of an indicator assignment for the specified time period that can be used to track the performance of the indicator.

Individual.description: Represents a customer’s data privacy and protection preferences. Data privacy records based on the Individual object store your customers’ preferences. Data privacy records are associated with related leads, contacts, person accounts, and users.

IndividualApplication.description: Represents an application form submitted by an individual or organization.

IndividualApplicationItem.description: Captures individual application input data that is used during run-time.

IndividualApplicationTask.description: Represents a task related to an application.

IndividualApplnParticipant.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a individual application.

IndividualHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to values in the fields of a data privacy record, based on the Individual object.

IndividualShare.description: Represents a list of access levels to a data privacy record along with an explanation of the access level. For example, if you have access to a record because you own it, the IndividualAccessLevel is All and RowCause is Owner.

InflationRate.description: Represents the inflation rates that are used to adjust currency values from one year to another.

InfoAuthRequestForm.description: Tracks the individual Authorization Form Texts that belong to an Authorization Request. For example, consent on GDPR privacy policy document and consent on mortgage loan rate lock fee document.

InfoAuthorizationRequest.description: Tracks a request for authorization on a Data Use Purpose. For example, consent request to share the documents required to open a financial account and share loan rate lock disclosure to the external customer.

InfoLibraryExternalDocument.description: Represents the external document that's used to collaborate on Information Library content.

InformationVerification.description: Represents the details of the information verification initiated for an object.

InsPlcyLimit.description: Represents the data that's used as a base to track the insurance policy consumption.

InsPlcyLimitTracking.description: Represents the calculated values based on the consumption of the policy and coverage attributes during claims processing.

InsPolicyAssetAttribute.description: Represents attributes for insurance policy asset.

InsPolicyAssetRelatedObj.description: Represents the relationship between an Insurance Policy Asset and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on Insurance Policy Asset.

InsPolicyCoverageAttribute.description: Represents attributes for insurance policy coverage.

InsPolicyCvrRelatedObj.description: Represents the relationship between an Insurance Policy Coverage and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on Insurance Policy Coverage.

InsPolicyParticipantAttr.description: Represents attributes for insurance policy participant.

InsPolicyPtcpRelatedObj.description: Represents the relationship between an Insurance Policy Participant and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on Insurance Policy Participant.

InsPolicyRelatedObject.description: Represents the relationship between an Insurance Policy and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on Insurance Policy.

InsPolicyTransactionDetail.description: Represents the details of an insurance policy transaction.

Insecure External Assets Event Type.description: Insecure External Assets events contain information about external assets. External assets include images or videos accessed by users over an insecure HTTP protocol. The event lists all your Salesforce pages that contain assets hosted insecurely on third-party sites that users loaded with a Chrome, Firefox, Microsoft Edge, or Safari browser. The INSECURE_URI field contains the URI being used to load the asset insecurely.

InspectionAssessmentInd.description: Represents the assessment indicators recorded during an inspection.

InspectionType.description: Represents the type of inspections related to a permit or license.

Insufficient Access Event Type.description: Insufficient Access events contain details about errors relating to insufficient record access, so that you can troubleshoot and resolve access issues for your users.

InsufficientAccessEventLog.description: Insufficient Access event logs contain details about errors relating to insufficient record access

InsuranceClaimAsset.description: A junction object that associates the Claim object with the InsurancePolicyAsset object. You see this object only if you have enabled the Use Many-to-Many Relationships org pref.

InsuranceContract.description: Represents insurance-specific contract information. Extension of Contract object, specifically for the insurance industry.

InsurancePolicy.description: Represents a type of insurance policy. Available with the Provider Network Management permission set license.

InsurancePolicyAsset.description: Represents the customer property insured through the insurance policy.

InsurancePolicyCoverage.description: A junction object that associates the InsurancePolicy object with the ProductCoverage object.

InsurancePolicyMemberAsset.description: A junction object that associates the InsurancePolicyAsset object with the InsurancePolicyParticipant object. You see this object only if you’ve enabled the Use Many-to-Many Relationships org pref.

InsurancePolicyParticipant.description: A junction object that associates the InsurancePolicy object with the Account object. This object represents the participants of an insurance policy. Insurance policy participants include policy owners and beneficiaries.

InsurancePolicySurcharge.description: Represents the charges calculated for an insurance policy and its related assets, coverages, and participants in a region.

InsurancePolicyTransaction.description: Represents a transaction related to a change that affects the premium of an insurance policy, such as an endorsement, renewal, or cancellation.

InsuranceProfile.description: Represents the insurance-related attributes for the insured member.

IntakeFormSection.description: Represents a section of an intake form such as a job application, a complaint, or a referral.

IntakeFormSectionPtcp.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to an intake form section.

IntegrationProviderAttr.description: Represents information about the attributes that are used in the definition for an integration provider.

IntegrationProviderDcsnRqmt.description: Represents a decision requirement used to create integration provider records.

IntegrationProviderDef.description: Represents the definition that's applicable to an integration provider.

IntegrationProviderExecution.description: Represents the execution instance of an integration provider.

Interaction.description: Represents an interaction (phone call, in-person meeting, or video conference) between two or more people (attendees), typically including at least one representative and one customer or partner.

InteractionAttendee.description: Represents an attendee of an interaction.

InteractionParticipant.description: Represents a user or User Group with whom the interaction is shared.

InteractionRelatedAccount.description: Represents a junction between an interaction and account that's related to that interaction.

InteractionSumDiscussedAccount.description: Represents information about the companies discussed in an interaction.

InteractionSummary.description: Represents the summary of an interaction, including confidentiality information.

InteractionSummaryParticipant.description: Represents a user with whom an interaction summary is shared.

InternalOrganizationUnit.description: Represents an organization that an Employee belongs to.

InteropTopic.description: Represents the interoperability topic for which notifications are sent to subscribers.

InteropTopicDetail.description: Represents the details of an interoperability topic.

InteropTopicFilter.description: Represents the properties by which an interoperability topic's notification can be filtered.

InteropTopicNtfcnResource.description: Represents the notification resource for an interoperability topic.

InteropTopicSubcrFilter.description: Represents the subscriber's criteria for filtering the interoperability topic subscription event.

InteropTopicSubcrParameter.description: Represents the parameters added to an interoperability topic subscription.

InteropTopicSubscription.description: Represents a subscription to an interoperability topic.

InteropTopicSubscriptionDtl.description: Represents the details of an interoperability topic subscription.

InteropTopicTriggerCriteria.description: Represents the criteria that trigger a notification for an interoperability topic.

InventoryCntProdtBatchItem.description: Represents the inventory count of a batch of a product at a location.

InventoryCntSerializedProdt.description: Represents a serialized product in an inventory count.

InventoryCountAssessment.description: Represents an inventory count performed at a location.

InventoryCountPlan.description: Represents a plan to count inventory at a location.

InventoryCountPlanItem.description: Represents a product in an inventory plan. Inventory Count Plan Item is the child object of Inventory Count Plan.

InventoryCountProductItem.description: Represents the inventory count of a product at a location. Inventory Count Product Item is a child object of Inventory Count.

InventoryItemReservation.description: Used to store inventory item reservation information for a specific product and location.

InventoryReplenishmentPolicy.description: Represents a policy for replenishing inventory when the inventory quantity reaches a minimum level.

InventoryReservation.description: Stores information about the status of cart inventory reservations in B2B and D2C Commerce.

InvocableActionEventLog.description: Invocable Action events capture the calls to Salesforce Invocable Actions.This is particularly useful to monitor actions invoked during Agentforce flows.

Invoice.description: Represents a financial document describing the total amount a buyer must pay for goods or services provided.

InvoiceBatchRun.description: Represents a batch processing job in Subscription Management or Billing (Revenue Cloud). During an invoice batch run, all billing schedules that meet the specified criteria are processed, resulting in the generation of invoices.

InvoiceBatchRunCriteria.description: Represents a batch processing job and its required criteria in Subscription Management. During an invoice batch run, all billing schedules that meet the specified criteria are processed, resulting in the generation of invoices.

InvoiceBatchRunRecovery.description: Provides information about an invoice batch run recovery procedure.

InvoiceDocument.description: Tracks and displays the status of documents generated for invoices. Invoice documents are available in the related lists of invoice entity records.

InvoiceLine.description: Represents the amount that a buyer must pay for a product, service, or fee. Invoice lines are created based on the amount of an order line.

InvolvementGroup.description: Represents an involvement group in an institution.

InvolvementGroupMember.description: Represents a member in an institution's involvement group.

JobApplnSearchableField.description: Represents searchable data for job applications, enabling criteria-based search and filtering to find applications that match the user-specific criteria.

JobExpenseType.description: Represents a unique expense type associated with a standard job in an organization, which is used to measure the job costs and budget.

JobPosition.description: Represents an instance of employment in a particular position in the organization.

JobPositionPayGrade.description: Represents a junction between a job position and a position pay grade.

JobPositionQualification.description: Represents qualification required for a specific job position. For example, Data Visualization for a Program and Management Analyst position.

JobPostingSearchableField.description: Object used for searching and Filtering published Job Postings.

JobProfile.description: Represents a job profile used for shift scheduling.

JobProfileQueueGroup.description: JobProfileQueueGroup defines the mapping between Queue and JobProfile and configurations for capacity plans in Workforce Engagement.

JobPstnRecruitmentRqs.description: Represents a junction between a job position and a recruitment requisition.

JournalReason.description: Represents a view that specifies the reason for the action that created a transaction journal.

JournalSubType.description: Represents the subcategory of transaction journal.

JournalType.description: Represents the category of transactions. For example: accrual, redemption.

Knowledge Article View Event Type.description: Knowledge Article View events contain user activity with your knowledge base.

KnowledgeArticle.description: Provides read-only access to an article and the ability to delete the primary article.

KnowledgeArticleEventLog.description: Knowledge Article View event logs contain user activity with your knowledge base.

KnowledgeArticleFeedback.description: Represents information about feedback from users on Knowledge articles and details about assignment of feedback to the article owner or team to take action.

KnowledgeArticleVersion.description: Provides a global view of standard article fields across all types of articles depending on their version.

KnowledgeArticleVersionHistory.description: Enables read-only access to the full history of an article.

KnowledgeArticleViewStat.description: Provides certain statistics related to the number of views for the specified article across all article types.

KnowledgeArticleVoteStat.description: Provides the weighted rating for the specified article on a scale of 1 to 5 across all article types.

Knowledge__DataCategorySelection.description: Represents a data category that classifies an article

Knowledge__Feed.description: Represents the feed for a knowledge article.

Knowledge__ka.description: Provides access to the concrete object that represents a Knowledge article, the parent object for article versions.

Knowledge__kav.description: Provides access to the concrete object that represents a Knowledge article version.

KnowledgeableUser.description: Represents a user identified as knowledgeable about a specific topic, and ranks them relative to other knowledgeable users.

LaborUnion.description: Represents the labor union organization that field technician is associated with. This association decides the wage classification, pay type, overtime code, supplemental compensation and wage calculation rules.

LandingPage.description: Represents an Account Engagement landing page. A landing page is a web page that a visitor reaches after clicking a link or advertisement. Landing pages can be created in Account Engagement and synced to Salesforce or created on the Landing Page object in Account Engagement Lightning App.

LeadCleanInfo.description: Stores the metadata Data.com Clean uses to determine a lead record’s clean status. Helps you automate the cleaning or related processing of lead records.

LeadDailyMetric.description: Represents the daily engagement metrics for a lead.

LeadLineItem.description: Represents items such as vehicles, accessories, and parts that a lead is interested in.

LeadMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for a lead.

LeadOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a lead with users other than the owner.

LeadPreferredSeller.description: Represents the relationship between a lead and the dealer account that the lead selects, or the relationship between a lead and the account that provides the lead.

LeadShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a Lead.

LeadStatus.description: Represents the status of a Lead record, such as Open, Qualified, or Converted.

LeadTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Lead.

LearnerPathway.description: Represents the learner's planned path to completion of their enrolled learning programs.

LearnerPathwayItem.description: Represents a requirement with completion details in the Learner Pathway.

LearnerProfile.description: Represents information about a learner's profile.

LearnerProgram.description: Represents details of a Learning Program Plan that's created for a learner.

LearnerProgramRequirement.description: Represents details of the requirement that a learner is required to complete in their assigned Learning Program Plan.

LearnerProgramRqmtProgress.description: Represents information about the progress of a requirement that a learner is required to complete as a part of the assigned program plan.

Learning.description: Represents information that defines a training that can be made available as a course, program, or on-site experience, for a contact.

LearningAchievement.description: Represents information about the outcome of a learning activity.

LearningAchievementConfig.description: Represents the mapping details between a Learning Achievement type and a Learning Achievement record type.

LearningContent.description: Represents a Trailhead or enablement site (myTrailhead) module assigned to a user in Workforce Engagement or Learning Paths. This object also represents a Trailhead module or video in an Enablement program exercise.

LearningCourse.description: Represents information about a course that’s required in a learning framework.

LearningEquivalency.description: Represents the details of the equivalency between external and internal learnings.

LearningEqvAchvMapping.description: Represents the mapping between a learning equivalency, internal achievement group, and external achievement group.

LearningFoundationItem.description: Represents information about the prerequisite, co-requisite, or the recommended learning that’s required for a learning outcome.

LearningItem.description: Represents an item that requires users to take action, including a Learning Paths entry, an Enablement program, or an exercise with linked content in an Enablement program. For Learning Paths, users are assigned a learning item to complete. For Enablement programs and exercises, users are assigned a program or can self-enroll in shared programs.

LearningItemAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a Learning Paths entry to users or groups or the enrollment of an Enablement program for a specific user.

LearningItemProgress.description: Represents the progress that a user has made towards completing an assigned learning item, such as a Learning Paths entry or Enablement program.

LearningItemSubmission.description: Represents a link to a resource, such as a video recording, that a user submits as part of a Feedback Request exercise in an Enablement program. For peer and manager feedback, this resource can be a recording of a user’s sales patch. For Einstein Coach feedback, this resource can be a video call, and Einstein generates feedback from the call’s transcription.

LearningItemType.description: Represents a custom exercise type that an Enablement user takes in an Enablement program in the Guidance Center. A custom exercise type also requires a corresponding LearningItem record for the Guidance Center and corresponding EnblProgramTaskDefinition and EnblProgramTaskSubCategory records for when admins create a program in Program Builder.

LearningOutcomeItem.description: Represents information about the mapping between the learnings and the related outcome.

LearningPathwayTemplate.description: Represents a template that a learner can apply to create a planned learning path.

LearningPathwayTemplateItem.description: Represents a requirement with completion details in the Learning Pathway Template.

LearningPathwayTmplPgmPlan.description: Represents a junction between Learning Program Plan and Learning Pathway Template objects.

LearningPractice.description: Represents a Feedback Request exercise in an Enablement program. Users can submit a sample of their work and request feedback from their peers and managers. Or, users can submit a video call and Einstein Coach generates feedback from the call’s transcription.

LearningProgram.description: Represents information about one or more trainings in a program that’s required to obtain a credential.

LearningProgramPlan.description: Represents details of a plan that’s created to execute a Learning Program.

LearningProgramPlanRqmt.description: Represents information about the requirements of a learning outcome that’s included in the learning program plan.

LearningRule.description: Represents a junction between the Learning and Rule (Expression Set) objects for an extensible rule on a learning.

LegalEntity.description: Represents the way an organization is structured. An organization can be a single legal entity or it can comprise more than one legal entity.

LicenseDefinitionCustomPermission (Devel.description: Represents a licensed custom permission that controls access to a license's features when included in a custom permission set license definition.

Lightning Error Event Type.description: Lightning Error events represent errors that occurred during user interactions with Lightning Experience and the Salesforce mobile app.

Lightning Interaction Event Type.description: Lightning Interaction events track user actions in Lightning Experience and the Salesforce mobile app, such as the user clicking, tapping, or scrolling on a page.

Lightning Logger Event Type.description: Lightning Logger events contain information from observed Lightning component logs. This event type is available in the EventLogFile object in API version 58.0 and later.

Lightning Page View Event Type.description: Lightning Page View events represent information about the page on which the event occurred in Lightning Experience and the Salesforce mobile app, such as the page's load time.

Lightning Performance Event Type.description: Lightning Performance events track trends in Lightning Experience and Salesforce mobile app performance.

LightningErrorEventLog.description: Lightning Error events represent errors that occurred during user interactions with Lightning Experience and the Salesforce mobile app.

LightningExitByPageMetrics.description: Represents frequency metrics about the standard pages within which users switched from Lightning Experience to Salesforce Classic.

LightningExperienceTheme.description: Represents information for a theme in Lightning Experience.

LightningLoggerEventLog.description: Lightning Logger Event Log provides information from observed Lightning component logs.

LightningOnboardingConfig.description: Represents the feedback provided when users switch from Lightning Experience to Salesforce Classic. Admins can customize the question, how frequently the form appears, and where the feedback is stored in Chatter from the Adoption Assistance page in Lightning Experience Setup.

LightningPageViewEventLog.description: Lightning Page View event logs represent information about the page on which the event occurred in Lightning Experience and the Salesforce mobile app. A Lightning Page View event log tracks the page a user visited, how long the user spent on the page, and the load time for the page.

LightningPrfmEventLog.description: Lightning Performance events track trends in Lightning Experience and Salesforce mobile app performance.

LightningToggleMetrics.description: Represents users who switched from Lightning Experience back to Salesforce Classic.

LightningUsageByAppTypeMetrics.description: Represents number of users on Lightning Experience and Salesforce Mobile.

LightningUsageByBrowserMetrics.description: Represents Lightning Experience usage grouped by user’s browser.

LightningUsageByFlexiPageMetrics.description: Represents custom pages users viewed most frequently in Lightning Experience.

LightningUsageByPageMetrics.description: Represents standard pages users viewed most frequently in Lightning Experience.

LinkedArticle.description: Represents a knowledge article that is attached to a work order, work order line item, or work type.

LinkedArticleFeed.description: Represents the comment feed on a linked article.

LinkedArticleHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a linked article.

ListEmail.description: Represents a list email sent from Salesforce, or sent from Account Engagement and synced to Salesforce. When the list email is sent, the recipients are generated by combining recipients in ListEmailIndividualRecipients and ListEmailRecipientSource. Duplicate and other invalid recipients are removed. The result is the recipients sent any given list email. ListEmail has a one-to-many relationship with ListEmailRecipientSource and ListEmailIndividualRecipient.

ListEmailIndividualRecipient.description: For a list email in Salesforce, represents a recipient. Each record represents a link from a list email to exactly one recipient for that list email. Recipients can be contacts, leads, or campaign members. Has a one-to-many relationship with ListEmail.

ListEmailMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for a single list email.

ListEmailRecipientSource.description: For a list email in Salesforce, represents the dynamically defined sources of recipient email addresses. Each record represents a link to a single list view or campaign that is examined when the list email is sent. Has a one-to-many relationship with ListEmail.

ListView.description: Represents a list view. A list view shows a set of records for an object, based on specific criteria.

ListViewChart.description: Represents a graphical chart that’s displayed on Salesforce for Android, iOS, and mobile web list views. The chart aggregates data that is filtered based on the list view that’s currently displayed.

ListViewChartInstance.description: Retrieves metadata for all standard and custom charts for a given entity in context of a given list view.

LiveAgentSession.description: This object is automatically created for each Chat session and stores information about the session.

LiveAgentSessionHistory.description: This object is automatically created for each Chat session and stores information about changes made to the session.

LiveAgentSessionShare.description: This object is automatically created for each Chat session and stores information about the session.

LiveChatBlockingRule.description: Represents a rule for blocking chat visitors’ IP addresses from starting new chats with agents.

LiveChatButton.description: Represents a button that allows visitors to request chats with Chat users.

LiveChatButtonDeployment.description: Associates an automated chat invitation with a specific deployment.

LiveChatButtonSkill.description: Represents all the skills available to a LiveChatButton except the one currently assigned. To retrieve the skill currently assigned, query LiveChatButton.

LiveChatDeployment.description: Represents the general settings for deploying Live Agent on a website.

LiveChatObjectAccessConfig.description: Represents the action you can perform on a specified object by the Chat API.

LiveChatObjectAccessDefinition.description: Represents the parent record for one or more LiveChatObjectAccessConfig objects.

LiveChatSensitiveDataRule.description: Represents a rule for masking or deleting data of a specified pattern. Written as a regular expression (regex).

LiveChatTranscript.description: This object is automatically created for each Live Agent chat session and stores information about the session.

LiveChatTranscriptEvent.description: Captures specific events that occur over the lifetime of a chat.

LiveChatTranscriptShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a LiveChatTranscript object.

LiveChatTranscriptSkill.description: Represents a join between LiveChatTranscript and Skill.

LiveChatUserConfig.description: Represents a setting that controls the console settings for Chat users.

LiveChatUserConfigProfile.description: Represents a join between LiveChatUserConfig and Profile.

LiveChatUserConfigUser.description: Represents a join between Live Chat User Config and User.

LiveChatVisitor.description: Represents a website visitor who has started or tried to start a chat session.

LoanApplicant.description: Represents details of the borrower or co-borrower for the loan application.

LoanApplicantAddress.description: Represents borrower's or co-borrower's current address information.

LoanApplicantAsset.description: Represents a junction between a borrower and a loan application asset.

LoanApplicantDeclaration.description: Represents financial issues like foreclosure, lawsuits, or defaults of the applicant or co-applicant.

LoanApplicantEmployment.description: Represents details about the borrower's or co-borrower's current and past employment.

LoanApplicantIncome.description: Represents details about the borrower and co-borrower current monthly income.

LoanApplicantLiability.description: Represents a junction between a borrower and a loan application liability.

LoanApplicationAsset.description: Represents details about the borrower's and co-borrower's current personal and real property.

LoanApplicationFinancial.description: Represents transaction details for a loan application.

LoanApplicationLiability.description: Represents details about the borrower and co-borrower current liabilities.

LoanApplicationProperty.description: Represents details of the property the loan application finances.

LoanApplicationTitleHolder.description: Represents details of borrowers who are applying to hold title to the property the loan application finances.

LocWaitlistMsgTemplate.description: Represents a junction object connecting LocationWaitlist to MessagingTemplate.

Location.description: Represents a warehouse, service vehicle, work site, or other element of the region where your team performs field service work. In API version 49.0 and later, you can associate activities with specific locations. Activities, such as the tasks and events related to a location, appear in the activities timeline when you view the location detail page. Also in API version 49.0 and later, Work.com users can view Employees as a related list on Location records. In API version 51.0 and later, this object is available for Omnichannel Inventory and represents physical locations where inventory is available for fulfilling orders.

LocationGroup.description: Represents a group of Omnichannel Inventory locations, providing an aggregate view of inventory availability across those locations. Omnichannel Inventory can create an inventory reservation for an order at the location group level, then assign the reservation to one or more locations in the group as needed.

LocationGroupAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a location to a location group.

LocationShippingCarrierMethod.description: The available shipping carrier services associated with a location or location group. Allows the assignment of different shipping methods to a specific location and enables flexibility and customization in the shipping process.

LocationTrustMeasure.description: Represents the COVID safety protocols that your business follows. For example, enforcement of masks, social distancing, cleanliness, and capacity limits.

LocationUse.description: Records the general purpose of the Location.

LocationWaitlist.description: Represents a queue created for a specific location. Multiple queues can be created for a single location. For example, you can have a queue for each sales agent or a standard queue and a queue for vulnerable groups. The specific party of people in a queue is represented by LocationWaitlistedParty.

LocationWaitlistedParty.description: Represents a specific party of people waiting in a queue.

Login As Event Type.description: Login As events contain details about what a Salesforce admin did while logged in as another user.

Login Event Type.description: Login events contain details about your org’s user login history.

LoginAsEventLog.description: LoginAsEventLog contains details about when a user logs in as another user in your org.

LoginEvent.description: The documentation has moved to LoginEvent in the Platform Events Developer Guide.

LoginEventLog.description: Login event logs contain details about your Salesforce org's user login history.

LoginGeo.description: Represents the geographic location of the user’s IP address for a login event. Due to the nature of geolocation technology, the accuracy of geolocation fields (for example, country, city, postal code) may vary.

LoginHistory.description: Represents the login history for all successful and failed login attempts for organizations and enabled portals.

LogoutEventLog.description: Contains details of user sessions ending or being revoked.

LogoutEventStream.description: The documentation has moved to LogoutEventStream in the Platform Events Developer Guide.

LookedUpFromActivity.description: This read-only object is displayed as a related list on an activity record (an event or a task); the list contains records that have custom lookup relationships from the activity to another object. This object is not queryable.

Loyalty Management Fields on EngagementC.description: Standard fields extend the EngagementChannelType object for use in Loyalty Management to represent to information promotion eligibility criteria.

Loyalty Management Fields on InternalOrg.description: Standard fields extend the InternalOrganizationUnit object for use in Loyalty Management to represent to information about Global Promotion Management’s connection with a Marketing Cloud business unit.

LoyaltyAggrPointExprLedger.description: Represents information about non-qualifying currency points that expire based on a fixed model tier group.

LoyaltyLedger.description: Records the points that have been credited or debited for a member across the transactions.

LoyaltyLedgerTraceability.description: Represents a tracker for the loyalty ledger. The debit ledger consumes points from the linked credit ledger for a member redemption or an accrual cancellation.

LoyaltyMemberCurrency.description: Represents the information about point balance for a member and a particular currency.

LoyaltyMemberTier.description: Represents information about the current tier of the member across tier groups.

LoyaltyMembershipLifecycle.description: Represents information about a member's lifecycle in the loyalty program.

LoyaltyPartnerProduct.description: Represents products and product categories offered by loyalty partners.

LoyaltyPgmCurrencySubtype.description: Represents a subtype of a fixed-model non-qualifying loyalty program currency.

LoyaltyPgmEngmtAttrProm.description: Represents a junction between Loyalty Program Engagement Attribute and Promotion. Associate an engagement attribute with a promotion if you want to track the engagement attribute during the promotion period.

LoyaltyPgmEngmtAttribute.description: Represents information about an engagement attribute for a loyalty program.

LoyaltyPgmGroupMbrRlnsp.description: Represents a junction between a Corporate or Individual type loyalty program member who is part of a group and the Group type loyalty program member.

LoyaltyPgmMbrAttributeVal.description: Represents information about the value reached by a loyalty program member for an engagement attribute.

LoyaltyPgmMbrPromEligView.description: Represents a virtual object that provides a consolidated view of the loyalty program member’s eligibility for a promotion and their enrollment status in eligible promotions.

LoyaltyPgmPartnerCurrency.description: Represents a junction between a loyalty program partner and a loyalty program currency.

LoyaltyPgmPartnerPromotion.description: Represents a junction between the Promotion and Loyalty Program Partner objects.

LoyaltyPgmPtnrLdgrSummary.description: Represents the aggregated ledger used by a loyalty program to credit points to or debit points from a prepaid partner's points pack. This ledger can also be used to add or deduct the monetary value of points from the postpaid partner's bill.

LoyaltyPgmPtnrPrepaidPack.description: Represents information about a prepaid set of points purchased by a loyalty program partner.

LoyaltyProgram.description: Represents the loyalty program within an organization. All the information related to members, tiers, tier groups, program currencies, vouchers, benefits, partners, promotions, transactions are associated with the program.

LoyaltyProgramBadge.description: Represents information about the badge that's associated with a loyalty program.

LoyaltyProgramCurrency.description: Represents qualifying and non-qualifying currencies associated with the program. Qualifying currency represents the engagement of a member with the program and it’s associated with a tier group. Non-qualifying currency represent the points that the member earns for redemption.

LoyaltyProgramCurrencyTier.description: Repesents a junction between non-qualifying loyalty program currency and loyalty tier.

LoyaltyProgramMbrPromotion.description: Represents details about the promotions to be applied for a loyalty program member. Tracks the enrollment status, promotion status, and progress for a promotion of a member.

LoyaltyProgramMember.description: Represents information about member who belongs to a loyalty program. The member can be individual or corporate type.

LoyaltyProgramMemberBadge.description: Represents a badge that’s assigned to a loyalty program member.

LoyaltyProgramMemberCase.description: Represents a junction between a loyalty program member and a case.

LoyaltyProgramMemberMerge.description: Represents information about merged loyalty program memberships.

LoyaltyProgramPartner.description: Represents partners that are associated with a given loyalty program. Partners can be an accrual partner, a redemption partner, or both.

LoyaltyProgramPartnerLedger.description: Represents the ledger used by a loyalty program to credit points to or debit points from a prepaid partner's points pack or from a postpaid partner’s point balance. This ledger can also be used to add or deduct the monetary value of points from the partner's postpaid bill.

LoyaltyProgramProcess.description: Represents information about loyalty program processes that determine how transaction journals are processed.

LoyaltyProgramWidget.description: Represents the configuration of a widget that a user can apply to the out-of-the-box widget templates and FlexCards provided by Omnistudio. The configuration helps implement custom UI changes, such as promotion type, promotion tag line, and so on for a user.

LoyaltyTier.description: Represents information about tiers of a loyalty program. A tier group has a set of tiers in a sequential order.

LoyaltyTierBenefit.description: A junction object that associates the loyalty benefits with the loyalty program tiers.

LoyaltyTierGroup.description: Represents information about tier groups of a loyalty program. Tier group categorizes members based on their loyalty points.

LoyaltyTierMshpFeeOption.description: Represents the options by which members can pay for tier or club memberships.

LoyaltyTierPromotion.description: Represents a junction between a member tier and a loyalty promotion.

MLField.description: Represents a single field in a data definition.

MLModel.description: Represents an AI model that can be used in Einstein Prediction Builder, Einstein Recommendation Builder, and other Einstein features.

MLModelFactor.description: Represents a field value that has a positive or negative effect on the model’s score.

MLModelFactorComponent.description: Represents information about the related MLModelFactor. For example, this object can represent a field value or a field range such as “Title = CEO” or “Annual Revenue >10000000”.

MLModelMetric.description: Represents a metric or statistic about the related model, such as accuracy, precision, or RSquared. Use a model’s metrics to learn about its performance and to compare it with other models.

MLPredictionDefinition.description: Represents a prediction definition that specifies details about the prediction.

Macro.description: Represents a macro, which is a set of instructions that tells the system to perform one or more tasks.

MacroInstruction.description: Represents an instruction in a macro. An instruction can specify the object that the macro interacts with, the context or publisher that the macro works within, the operation or action that the macro performs, and the target of the macro’s actions.

MacroUsage.description: Represents macro usage on a record, including which macro was used, who used it, and how they used it.

MailmergeTemplate.description: Represents a mail merge template (a Microsoft Word document) used for performing mail merges for your organization.

MaintenanceAsset.description: Represents an asset covered by a maintenance plan in field service. Assets can be associated with multiple maintenance plans.

MaintenanceWorkRule.description: Represents the recurrence pattern for a maintenance record.

ManagedCareProgramPrfm.description: Represents the rating and enrollee retention rate according to the plan type of an average medicare advantage plan.

ManagedContent.description: Represents managed content in a Salesforce CMS workspace for use in an Experience Cloud site or a channel. The ManagedContent object represents the complete instance of a managed content record. It provides a consistent identifier for the managed content so that variants of the content item can be created over time.

ManagedContentChannel.description: Represents the details of a CMS channel. CMS channels correspond to managed content publishing endpoints. They deliver published content from your Salesforce CMS workspaces to an audience.

ManagedContentInfo.description: Allows the creation of relationship to Product using ProductMedia.

ManagedContentSpace.description: Represents the complete instance of a Salesforce CMS workspace that stores managed content. Users and groups with designated permissions can access and manage the content in a CMS workspace.

ManagedContentVariant.description: Represents a variant of a managed content item.

ManufacturingProgram.description: Represents information about a manufacturing program. For example, Verican X program for Verican Account to manufacture auto components for their upcoming concept vehicle, staring from 01-Jan-2022 and valid until 01-Dec-2024.

MarketingForm.description: Represents an Account Engagement marketing form that has been synched to Salesforce. Use forms on your website and landing pages to collect information about visitors and turn anonymous visitors into identified prospects.

MarketingLink.description: Represents an Account Engagement marketing link record, either a custom redirect or a file, that has been synced to Salesforce.

MatchingRule.description: Represents a matching rule that is used to identify duplicate records.

MatchingRuleItem.description: Represents criteria used by a matching rule to identify duplicate records.

MaterialityAssessment.description: Represents information about stakeholder engagement to assess the importance of environmental, social, and governance (ESG) issues for them.

MaterialityMatrixScore.description: Represents the materiality matrix score used to visualize all the data gathered through materiality assessment intake process.

MaterialityStakeholder.description: Represents information about a stakeholder who can be internal or external party having interest in a company. A stakeholder can either affect or be affected by the business.

MaterialityStkhldrCatg.description: Represents a category to organize materiality stakeholders into groups, such as employees, shareholders, suppliers, and customers.

MaterialityTopic.description: Represents a possible topic for materiality assessment.

MaterialityTopicDocClauseSet.description: Represents a reference object with information about the topic and a document clause set.

MaterialityTopicQstn.description: Represents the mapping between the materiality assessment topics and the materiality assessment survey questions.

MaterialityTopicReference.description: Represents a reference object with information about two related topics.

MedReconRecommendation.description: Stores information about a medication recommendation and associates a recommendation to a medication reconciliation.

MedReconStmtRecommendation.description: Associates a medication recommendation to a medication statement and medication reconciliation.

MedTherapyStmtReviewIssue.description: Represents a junction object between the Medication Therapy Statement Review and Clinical Detected Issue objects.

MedicationReconciliation.description: Stores information about a medication reconciliation conducted for a patient

MedicationTherapyReview.description: Stores information about a medication therapy review conducted for a patient.

MedicationTherapyStmtReview.description: Represents a junction object between the Medication Therapy Review and Medication Statement objects.

MemberBenefit.description: Represents details about a benefit that’s assigned to a loyalty program member and has a benefit action that’s triggered.

MemberPlan.description: Represents details about the insurance coverage for a member or subscriber.

MentoringProfile.description: Represents information for a participant in a mentoring program.

MerchAccPaymentMethodSet.description: Defines an ordered list of payment methods that are available to a merchant's cudstomer during checkout. You can configure multiple payment method sets, each designated for a specific locale, payment region, or sale channel.

MerchAccPaymentMethodType.description: Refers to a payment method that is in a payment method set, which is defined by the MerchAccPaymentMethodSet object.

MerchantAccount.description: A type of bank account that lets a merchant accept payments from a variety of payment methods, including credit or debit cards, or digital wallets. A Salesforce Payments merchant account is linked to an underlying payment gateway to process payments

MerchantAccountEvent.description: Represents a merchant account platform event. Subscribe to these events so you can listen and respond to them when they’re published. For example, create a Salesforce Flow that is triggered when one of these events is published.

MessagingChannel.description: Represents a communication channel that an end user can use to send a message to an agent. A communication channel can be an SMS number, a Facebook page, or another supported messaging channel.

MessagingChannelSkill.description: Junction object that represents an association between MessagingChannel and Skill.

MessagingChannelUsage.description: Represents the status of an enhanced Messaging channel or of an application in a Unified Messaging channel.

MessagingConfiguration.description: Represents the details for a Messaging configuration.

MessagingDeliveryError.description: Represents a log of triggered outbound failures to verify when a triggered outbound has failed.

MessagingEndUser.description: Represents a single address—such as a phone number or Facebook page—communicating with a single Messaging channel.

MessagingLink.description: Represents the link between a Messaging Channel and where it's shared.

MessagingSession.description: Represents a session on a Messaging channel.

MessagingSessionMetrics.description: Represents a metric gathered about a specific enhanced messaging session, such as average agent response time.

MessagingTemplate.description: Represents a Messaging template used to send pre-formatted messages.

Metadata API Operation Event Type.description: Metadata API Operation events contain details of Metadata API retrieval and deployment requests.

MetadataApiOpEventLog.description: MetadataApiOpEventLog stores details of Metadata API retrieval and deployment requests.

MetadataPackage.description: Represents a package that has been developed in the org you’re logged in to. Applies to unlocked, unmanaged, first-generation, and second-generation managed packages.

MetadataPackageVersion.description: Represents a package version (managed or unmanaged) that has been uploaded from the org you’re logged in to.

Metric.description: The Metric object represents the components of a goal metric such as its name, metric type, and current value.

MetricDataLink.description: The link between the metric and the data source, such as a report.

MfgPgmCpntFrcstFactOpptySchd.description: Represents a junction between the forecast and opportunity line item schedule objects, providing details on the relationship between forecast data and corresponding sales order schedules.

MfgProgramCpntFrcstFact.description: Represents information about the generated manufacturing program component forecast records.

MfgProgramForecastFact.description: Represents information about the generated manufacturing program forecast records.

MfgProgramTemplate.description: Represents information about the templates associated with a manufacturing program.

MfgProgramTemplateItem.description: Represents information about the transformation type associated with a manufacturing program template.

MfgProgramVariantFrcstFact.description: Represents information about the generated manufacturing program product variant forecast records.

MilestoneType.description: Represents a milestone (required step in a customer support process).

MktJourneyDcsnSetup.description: Represents a collection of Marketing Cloud Engagement journeys that you can interact with by using Salesforce Flow in Marketing Cloud.

MlIntentUtteranceSuggestion.description: Represents a customer input, used for training purposes in the feedback loop process of a conversation. Admins can add these inputs to the intent training model.

MobSecurityCertPinConfig.description: Configuration of mobile security certificate pinning on the Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile Security.

MobSecurityCertPinEvent.description: The event of mobile security certificate pinning on the Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile Security.

MobileDeviceAppRegistration.description: Represents the details provided in a mobile device registration event from an app that uses the Engagement Mobile SDK.

MobileSecurityAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of mobile security policies to a profile. The policies apply to the Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile App Security enabled.

MobileSecurityPolicy.description: Enables mobile security policies on the Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile Security.

MobileSecurityUserMetric.description: Represents the metrics for users who have Enhanced Mobile Security policies enforced.

MobileSettingsAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a particular field service mobile settings configuration to a user profile.

MonthlyUsageTrkgDataGap.description: Represents a gap in the tracking of fuel usage data for the month.

MsgChannelLanguageKeyword.description: Represents the consent configuration for a Messaging channel.

MsgChannelUsageExternalOrg.description: Represents the Enterprise ID (EID) and Business Unit (MID) for Marketing Cloud connections in a Unified Messaging channel.

Multiblock Report Event Type.description: Multiblock Report events contain details about Joined Report reports.

MultipartyInfoAuthRequest.description: Tracks a request for multiple parties of authorization on a Data Use Purpose. For example, consent requests to share the required documents to open a joint financial account or share mortgage disclosures to loan applicants (borrower + co-borrower).

MutingPermissionSet.description: Represents a set of disabled permissions and is used in conjunction with PermissionSetGroup.

MyDomainDiscoverableLogin.description: Represents configuration settings when the My Domain login page type is Discovery. Login Discovery provides an identity-first login experience, where the login page contains the identifier field only. Based on the identifier entered, a handler determines how to authenticate the user.

Name.description: Non-queryable object that provides information about foreign key traversals when the foreign key has more than one parent.

Named Credential Event Type.description: The Named Credential event type captures information about Apex callouts that use named credentials as their endpoints. Use this event type to audit the installed managed packages that use named credentials. If you don’t recognize the package namespace in the named credential event log file, then you can investigate whether a security breach has occurred.

NamedCredential.description: Represents a named credential, which specifies the URL of a callout endpoint and its required authentication parameters in one definition.

NamedCredentialEventLog.description: The Named Credential event type captures information about Apex callouts that use named credentials as their endpoints. Use this event type to audit the installed managed packages that use named credentials. If you don’t recognize the package namespace in the named credential event log file, then you can investigate whether a security breach has occurred.

NamespaceRegistry.description: Represents a namespace that you can link to scratch orgs that were created from your org’s Dev Hub. You use the namespace when developing, packaging, and releasing an app. You can’t create this object with the API. Use the Link Namespace action in the Dev Hub graphical interface to insert a NamespaceRegistry record.

NavigationLinkSet.description: Represents the navigation menu in an Experience Cloud site. A navigation menu consists of items that users can click to go to other parts of the site.

NavigationMenuItem.description: Represents a single menu item in a NavigationLinkSet. Use this object to create, delete, or update menu items in your Experience Cloud site’s navigation menu.

NavigationMenuItemLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a navigation menu item in an Experience Cloud site.

Network.description: Represents an Experience Cloud site. Salesforce Experience Cloud lets you create branded spaces for your employees, customers, and partners. You can customize and create experiences, whether they’re communities, sites, or portals, to meet your business needs, then transition seamlessly between them. Experience Cloud sites let you share information, records, and files with coworkers and stakeholders all in one place.

NetworkActivityAudit.description: Represents an audit trail of moderation actions in Experience Cloud sites.

NetworkAffinity.description: Represents a junction object that associates a user profile with a Network object, that is, with an Experience Cloud site. Use NetworkAffinity to assign a default Experience Cloud site to a user profile.

NetworkAuthApiSettings.description: Represents the settings that control enablement, access, and security for the Headless Registration Flow, Headless Forgot Password Flow, Headless Passwordless Login Flow, and their associated APIs.

NetworkDataCategory.description: Represents data categories in Lightning Web Runtime (LWR) Experience Cloud Sites.

NetworkDiscoverableLogin.description: Represents the Login Discoverable page from where customers and partners log in to an Experience Cloud site. Customers and partners are users with an External Identity license or any communities license for Experience Cloud.

NetworkEmailTmplAllowlist.description: Represents an allowlist for the one-time password (OTP) email templates that are sent to end users during the Headless Registration Flow, the Headless Passwordless Login Flow, and the Headless Forgot Password Flow.

NetworkFeedResponseMetric.description: Represents an object that stores the date and time values of question posts. It captures information for question creation, answer creation, and when an answer is marked as best answer

NetworkMember.description: Represents a member of an Experience Cloud site. Members can be either users in your company or external users with portal profiles.

NetworkMemberGroup.description: Represents a group of members in an Experience Cloud site. Members can be either users in your internal org or external users assigned portal profiles. An administrator adds members to an Experience Cloud site by adding a profile or a permission set, and any user with the profile or permission set becomes a member of the site. This object is available in API version 26.0 and later.

NetworkModeration.description: Represents a flag on an item in a community.

NetworkPageOverride.description: Represents information about custom pages used to override the default pages in Experience Cloud sites. You can create Experience Builder or Visualforce pages and override the default pages in a site. Using custom pages allows you to create a more personalized experience for your users.

NetworkReferencedObject.description: A junction object that associates the loyalty program with the Experience Cloud site.

NetworkSelfRegistration.description: Represents the account that self-registering Experience Cloud users are associated with by default.

NetworkUserHistoryRecent.description: Represents an Experience Cloud site user’s history of accessed records.

Note.description: Represents a note, which is text associated with a custom object or a standard object, such as a Contact, Contract, or Opportunity.

NoteAndAttachment.description: This read-only object contains all notes and attachments associated with an object.

NoteTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Note.

OSAsyncChgCompletedEvent.description: An event that allows the processing of the credit memo, invoices, and other entities after a bulk action has successfully completed. The event provides all of the values that would exist on the synchronous APIs. This object is available in API version 63.0 and later.

OauthCustomScope.description: Represents a permission defining the protected data that a connected app can access from an external entity when Salesforce is the OAuth authorization provider.

OauthCustomScopeApp.description: Represents the name of the connected app to which the custom scope is assigned.

OauthToken.description: Represents an OAuth access token for connected app authentication. Use this object to create a user interface for token management.

OauthTokenExchHandlerApp.description: Represents the enablement settings for a specific Salesforce connected app or external client app that’s enabled for the token exchange handler. A handler can be enabled for multiple apps.

OauthTokenExchangeHandler.description: Represents a token exchange handler. The token exchange handler also consists of an Apex class. During the OAuth 2.0 token exchange flow, the token exchange handler is used to validate tokens from an external identity provider and to map users to Salesforce.

ObjectDataImport.description: Represents the data import status of one or more object records.

ObjectDataImportReference.description: Represents the relationships to the associated reference objects showing the source from which the data is imported.

ObjectMetadataTag.description: Represents a meta tag for a store page. Meta tags in HTML documents provide structured data used by search engines for ranking and to show content in search results.

ObjectPermissions.description: Represents the enabled object permissions for the parent PermissionSet.

ObjectRelatedUrl.description: Represents a URL slug for a Product or Category page on a B2B Commerce or D2C Commerce LWR site, or a custom object, account, or contact page on an enhanced LWR Experience Cloud site.

ObjectTerritory2AssignmentRule.description: Represents a territory assignment rule that’s associated with an object, such as Account. ObjectTerritory2AssignmentRuleItem can be created or deleted if the BooleanFilter field on its corresponding ObjectTerritory2AssignmentRule is null.

ObjectTerritory2AssignmentRuleItem.description: A single row of selection criteria for an ObjectTerritory2AssignmentRule object. ObjectTerritory2AssignmentRuleItem can only be created or deleted if the BooleanFilter field on its corresponding ObjectTerritory2AssignmentRule object is a null value. Available if Sales Territories has been enabled.

ObjectTerritory2Association.description: Represents an association (by assignment) between a territory and an object record such as an account or a lead.

ObjectUserTerritory2View.description: Represents a user and object, such as an account or lead, assigned to a territory.

Occupation.description: Represents a group of positions that engage in a specialized line of work and require a connected set of skills, knowledge, or qualifications. For example, the occupation of Registered Nurses in the Healthcare occupation group.
