Scope 3 procurement summary quantifies the effect on atmospheric warming, represented in tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e) by using a matched emission factor from an associated Procurement Emission Factor Item record.

Scorecard.description: Use scorecards to measure partner performance and establish benchmarks for channel programs within Experience Cloud. Display any report summary results that your channel account manager or executive team wants to see.

ScorecardAssociation.description: Represents a connection between a specific scorecard and the associated account, channel program, or channel program level.

ScorecardMetric.description: Stores information about a Salesforce report that is run and summarized to get a single value. The stored value is added as a metric to the related Scorecard object.

ScratchOrgInfo.description: Represents a scratch org and its audit log. Use this object to create a scratch org and keep a log of its creation and deletion.

Search Click Event Type.description: Search Click events contain details about the user’s interaction with the search results in the search results page. Interactions with search results in the instant result dialog are not recorded by this event. All searches within the app, including Experience Cloud sites, are included. However, unauthenticated users won’t have a unique Salesforce user ID.

Search Event Type.description: Search events contain details about the user’s search query. All searches within the app, including Experience Cloud sites, are included. However, unauthenticated users won’t have a unique Salesforce user ID.

SearchActivity.description: Represents search activity on a Knowledge article. Also known as KnowledgeSearchActivity.

SearchClickEventLog.description: Search Click Event Log contains details about the user’s interaction with the search results.

SearchEventLog.description: Search Event Log provides details about the user’s search query.

SearchLayout.description: Represents a search layout defined for an object.

SearchPromotionRule.description: Represents a promoted search term, which is one or more keywords that you associate with a Salesforce Knowledge article. When a user’s search query includes these keywords, the associated article is returned first in search results.

SearchableReferenceDocument.description: Represents documents that are referenced to search for answers during documentation authoring, such as ESG disclosures.

SecuritiesHolding.description: Represents the securities associated with an insurance policy.

SecurityCustomBaseline.description: Provides the ability to read, create, and delete user-defined custom security baselines, which define an org’s security standards.

SelfServiceUser.description: Represents a Contact who has been enabled to use your organization’s Self-Service portal, where he or she can obtain online support.

Seller.description: Represents the seller role of an individual with respect to a particular company or organization.

SenderEmailAddress.description: Represents a From address in a marketing email.

SerializedProduct.description: Records serial numbers for each product in an inventory.

SerializedProductTransaction.description: Represents a change in the state of a serialized product.

ServiceAppointment.description: Represents an appointment booked through Salesforce Scheduler.

ServiceAppointmentAsset.description: Represents a junction between Service Appointment and Asset. This junction object enables admins to associate a patient appointment to an asset such as a piece of medical equipment.

ServiceAppointmentAttendee.description: Represents a Lead, Contact, or Person Account who is associated with the Service Appointment of type Group.

ServiceAppointmentEvent.description: Notifies subscribers of the service appointment details that are generated from the event platform.

ServiceAppointmentGroup.description: Stores information about a group of related service appointments.

ServiceAppointmentStatus.description: Represents a possible status of a service appointment in field service.

ServiceChannel.description: Represents a channel of work items that are received from your organization—for example, cases, chats, or leads.

ServiceChannelFieldPriority.description: Represents a secondary routing priority field-value mapping.

ServiceChannelStatus.description: Represents the status that’s associated with a specific service channel.

ServiceChannelStatusField.description: Represents the values that you use to indicate completed and in-progress work item status for the status field in the Status-Based Capacity routing model.

ServiceContract.description: Represents a customer support contract (business agreement).

ServiceContractOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a ServiceContract (customer service agreement) with users other than the owner.

ServiceCrew.description: Represents a group of service resources who can be assigned to service appointments as a unit.

ServiceCrewMember.description: Represents a technician service resource that belongs to a service crew.

ServiceCrewOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a service crew with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.

ServiceInfoRequestDetail.description: Represents additional details about a service information request, such as the detail type and detail code.

ServiceInfoRequestOperation.description: Represents the system operation performed for a service information request such as a session launch or a questionnaire package operation.

ServiceInfoRespOvrideOpt.description: Represents the possible reasons for overriding a service information response.

ServiceInfoRespResourceUrl.description: Represents the URLs of resources relevant to a service information response.

ServiceInfoRespSuggestion.description: Represents suggestions in a service information response. For example, suggesting a change in medication dosage.

ServiceInfoResponseAction.description: Represents actions to be performed as suggested by a service information response.

ServiceInfoResponseCoverage.description: Represents coverage details about a service information response. For example, if additional information or documentation is required for the coverage to be provided.

ServiceInfoRqstOpOutcome.description: Represents the outcome of a service information request operation.

ServiceInformationRequest.description: Represents information about a service information request, such as the date and time when the request was submitted and the type of service requested.

ServiceInformationResponse.description: Represents a response to a service information request.

ServicePoint.description: Represents an entry point for services to a premises. The service provided to each service point is separately metered (or measured). Useful for energy services including electricity, water and gas services.

ServicePresenceStatus.description: Represents a presence status that can be assigned to a service channel.

ServiceReport.description: Represents a report that summarizes a work order, work order line item, or service appointment.

ServiceReportLayout.description: Represents a service report template in field service.

ServiceResource.description: Represents a technician or an asset.

ServiceResourceCapacity.description: Represents the maximum number of scheduled hours or number of service appointments that a capacity-based service resource can complete within a specific time period.

ServiceResourceCapacityHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a service resource capacity record.

ServiceResourceCostRule.description: Represents the rules that calculate the value of a meal or equivalent gifts awarded to the field service worker.

ServiceResourceDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within a ServiceResource record’s fields.

ServiceResourceLeaveBalance.description: Stores the leave balances for service resources.

ServiceResourceOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a service resource with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.

ServiceResourcePreference.description: Represents the service resource scheduling preferences that are considered as a business objective in the scheduling logic engine.

ServiceResourceSkill.description: Represents a skill that a service resource possesses in Salesforce Scheduler.

ServiceSetupProvisioning.description: Represents a task completed by the Service Setup Assistant.

ServiceTerritory.description: Represents a geographic or functional region in which work can be performed in Salesforce Scheduler.

ServiceTerritoryDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within a ServiceTerritory record’s fields.

ServiceTerritoryLocation.description: Represents a location associated with a particular service territory in field service.

ServiceTerritoryMember.description: Represents a service resource who can be assigned to service appointments in a service territory in Salesforce Scheduler.

ServiceTerritoryRelationship.description: Represent the relationship between service territories based on work types performed.

ServiceTerritoryWorkType.description: Represents the relationship between a ServiceTerritory object and a WorkType object for Salesforce Scheduler appointments.

SessionPermSetActivation.description: The SessionPermSetActivation object represents a permission set assignment activated during an individual user session. When a SessionPermSetActivation object is inserted into a permission set, an activation event fires, allowing the permission settings to apply to the user’s specific session.

SetupAuditTrail.description: Represents changes you or other admins made in your org’s Setup area for at least the last 180 days.

SetupEntityAccess.description: Represents the enabled setup entity access settings (such as for Apex classes) for the parent PermissionSet.

ShapeRepresentation.description: Contains information about the shape of an org. The shape of an org includes licenses and limits information. You can easily create scratch orgs based on a source org’s shape.

SharedSavingPaymentAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Shared Saving Payment Agreement type.

SharingRecordCollectionItem.description: Represents a single record in a collection of records.

SharingRecordCollectionMember.description: Represents a user with access to a collection of records.

Shift.description: Represents a shift for service resource scheduling.

ShiftEngagementChannel.description: Represents the relationship between a Shift object and an Engagement Channel Type object for Salesforce Scheduler.

ShiftHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a time sheet.

ShiftOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a shift with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.

ShiftPattern.description: Represents a pattern of templates for creating shifts.

ShiftPatternEntry.description: ShiftPatternEntry links a shift template to a shift pattern.

ShiftSegment.description: Represents a scheduled activity within a shift.

ShiftSegmentType.description: Represents a type of activity scheduled within a shift.

ShiftShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a field service shift.

ShiftStatus.description: Represents a shift, such as Tentative, Published, or Confirmed.

ShiftTemplate.description: Represents a template for creating shifts.

ShiftWorkTopic.description: Represents the relationship between a Shift object and a Work Type or Work Type Group object for Salesforce Scheduler.

Shipment.description: Represents a product item that’s in transit between two inventory locations.

ShipmentItem.description: Represents a product that’s included in a shipment.

ShippingCarrier.description: Shipping company or carrier responsible for transporting goods or packages. Examples include UPS, FedEx, and USPS.

ShippingCarrierMethod.description: Shipping service provided by a shipping carrier. Examples include Ground, 2Day, and NextDay. Service depends on the range of transit times available for each carrier.

ShippingConfigSetProduct.description: Represents a product associated with a shipping configuration.

ShippingConfigurationSet.description: Shipping configuration for a set of products in a store.

ShippingRateArea.description: A designated geographical area that’s available for shipping.

ShippingRateGroup.description: Available shipping rates based on shipping destination.

SignatureTask.description: Represents the signature-related information that a visitor captures as part of a visit.

SignatureTaskLineItem.description: Represents a junction between a signature task and a digital signature captured in a visit.

SignupRequest.description: Represents a request for a new sign-up.

Site.description: Represents a public website that is integrated with an org.

SiteDetail.description: Represents the details of a Salesforce site or Experience Cloud site.

SiteEventLog.description: SiteEventLog stores details of Site.com requests. Requests can originate from the browser (UI).

SiteHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to the values in the fields of a site.

SiteIframeWhitelistUrl.description: Represents a list of external domains that you allow to frame your Salesforce site or Experience Cloud site pages.

SiteRedirectMapping.description: Represents a site redirect from an external site to an Experience Cloud site.

Sites Event Type.description: Sites events contain details of Site.com requests. Requests can originate from the browser (UI).

Skill.description: Represents a skill that service resources have.

SkillLevelDefinition.description: Represents a skill which can be acquired by completing enablement site (myTrailhead) modules.

SkillLevelProgress.description: Represents training progress for a given user.

SkillProfile.description: Represents a join between Skill and Profile.

SkillRequirement.description: Represents a skill that is required to complete a particular task in Salesforce Scheduler. Skill requirements can be added to work types Salesforce Scheduler.

SkillType.description: Represents the broader type or category that a skill belongs to.

SkillUser.description: Represents a join between Skill and User.

SlaProcess.description: Represents an entitlement process associated with an Entitlement.

Snippet.description: Represents a snippet, which is a container for rich text that can be reused across Account Engagement emails and email templates.

SnippetAssignment.description: Represents a relationship between a snippet and a campaign. Assignments are required to use snippet content in Account Engagement emails and email templates. A snippet can be assigned to more than one campaign.

SoapApiEventLog.description: SOAP API events contain details about your org's SOAP API request activity.

SocialContributionSum.description: Represents information about social contributions made to political and non-political organizations belonging to financial and non-financial categories.

SocialPersona.description: Represents a snapshot of a contact's profile on a social network such as Facebook or Twitter.

SocialPost.description: Represents a snapshot of a post on a social network such as a Facebook or Twitter.

Solution.description: Represents a detailed description of a customer issue and the resolution of that issue.

SolutionStatus.description: Represents the status of a Solution, such as Draft, Reviewed, and so on.

SolutionTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Solution.

StageTransitionEntry.description: Represents the information about the runtime instance of the object stage transition.

StampAssignment.description: Represents assignment of a User Specialty to a user.

StandardCareFeeAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Standard Care Fee Agreement type.

StandardInvocableActionType.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up granular user permissions for access to a standard invocable action in Flow Builder.

StandardShippingRate.description: Standard shipping rate for a store.

StaticResource.description: Represents a static resource that can be used in Visualforce markup.

StgTrnsUndwrEvaluation.description: Represents the underwriting rule evaluation result.

StnryAssetAnnualFact.description: Represents the information about stationary assets and their types, which is used to quantify the related intensity.

StnryAssetCrbnFtprnt.description: Represents the total carbon emissions and other environmental attributes from stationary assets. Carbon footprint quantifies the effect of atmospheric warming, which is represented in metric tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e). Additionally, it also quantifies various aspects of the energy performance of the asset.

StnryAssetCrbnFtprntItm.description: Represents the total tCO₂e emissions of individual fuel types, which are the child records of the stationary asset carbon footprint record.

StnryAssetEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to stationary assets across multiple fuel types.

StnryAssetEnvrSrc.description: Represents assets that are stationary in nature, use energy that can be recorded, and are the source of greenhouse gas emissions.

StnryAssetWaterActvty.description: Represents information about the water activities, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge that are related to the stationary assets.

StnryAssetWaterFtprnt.description: Represents information about the total volume of water from the water activities, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge that are related to the stationary assets.

StnryAssetWtrFtprntItm.description: Represents information about the total volume of water from each water activity, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge related to the stationary assets. Each water activity is a child record of the stationary asset water footprint object.

StoreActionPlanTemplate.description: Associate an action plan template with a store.

StoreAssortment.description: Associate an assortment to either a store, a store group, or an account.

StoreIntegratedService.description: Represents an association between an integration and a store.

StoreProduct.description: Associate a product to a retail store or to a specific in-store location.

StreamingChannel.description: Represents a channel that is the basis for notifying listeners of generic Streaming API events.

SuccessTeam.description: Records details about a success team in Salesforce Scheduler.

SuggestedAssessmentReason.description: Stores the reasons for a suggested assessment.

SupplementalCompensation.description: Represents the meals or equivalent gifts awarded to the field service worker according to the labor laws and company policies.

Supplier.description: Represents information about the supplier that’s related to a climate-committed company.

SupplierProduct.description: Represents information that's used to track the products that are purchased from a supplier.

Surcharge.description: Represents the details about a surcharge calculation.

SurveyEmailBranding.description: Represents the configuration settings for invitation emails sent to survey participants for a particular survey.

SurveyEngagementContext.description: Represents the context based on which a survey invitation was sent or a survey response was received.

SurveyInvitation.description: Represents the invitation sent to a participant to complete the survey.

SurveyPage.description: Represents a page, such as the title page or a question page, in a survey.

SurveyQuestion.description: Represents a question in a survey.

SurveyQuestionChoice.description: Represents an answer choice that a participant can select for a survey question.

SurveyQuestionResponse.description: Represents a participant’s answer to a specific question.

SurveyQuestionScore.description: Represents the aggregate of responses for the following question types: date, multiple choice, picklist, radio, ranking, rating, scoring, slider, and Net Promoter Score® (NPS®).

SurveyResponse.description: Represents information about a participant’s response to a survey, such as the status of the response, the participant’s location, and when the survey was completed.

SurveySubject.description: Represents a relationship between a survey and another object, such as an account or a case.

SurveyVersion.description: Represents a version of a survey.

SurveyVersionAddlInfo.description: Represents additional information about a survey version. This information defines the default settings of a survey version.

SustainabilityCredit.description: Represents information about the sustainability credits that are a part of a sustainability purchase.

SustainabilityPurchase.description: Represents information related to the sustainability credits purchases such as carbon credits.

SustainabilityScorecard.description: Represents information about the annual sustainability scorecard of third-party organizations whose data is used to calculate scope 3 emissions.

SustainabilityStakeholder.description: Represents the stakeholder for sustainability data, such as stakeholder for environmental, social, and governance data.

SustainabilityTask.description: Represents the tasks that the sustainability stakeholder does for a sustainability task group.

SustainabilityTaskGroup.description: Represents the group of sustainability tasks.

SustainabilityUom.description: Represents information about the additional unit of measure values defined by a customer.

SustnMaterialUseSummary.description: Represents the circular economy information that a company discloses as part of ESRS E5 - Resource use and circular economy.

SustnUomConversion.description: Represents information about the unit of measure conversion for the additional fuel types defined by a customer.

SvcApptSchdEvent.description: Represents the service appointment event. This object is included in a streamed notification received on the channels for the parent platform events. You can’t subscribe to the SvcApptSchdEvent channel directly.

SvcCatalogCategory.description: Represents a group of Service Catalog items by functional area.

SvcCatalogCategoryItem.description: Represents an association between a Service Catalog item and category. Service catalog items can be grouped into categories.

SvcCatalogFilterCriteria.description: Represents an eligibility rule that determines if a Service Catalog user has access to a catalog item.

SvcCatalogItemAttribute.description: Represents pre-filled fulfillment flow inputs and user questions to ask to users in the context of a service catalog item version.

SvcCatalogItemDef.description: Represents a service catalog item that can be requested by a service catalog user.

SvcCatalogItemDependency.description: Represents a collection of records that indicate the dependencies of a service process.

SvcCatalogReqRelatedItem.description: Represents an item related to a Service Catalog Request.

SvcCatalogRequest.description: Represents a request made by a user using the Service Catalog. Catalog builders use this object to report on Service Catalog activity.

SvcInfoRelatedQuestionnaire.description: Represents the questionnaire associated with a service information request or service information response coverage.

SvcInfoRespCoverageDetail.description: Represents additional coverage details about a service information response.

Swarm.description: Represents a team of agents, Salesforce users, or Slack users in a Slack channel or thread dedicated to solving a problem. This problem can be related to a support case, incident, sales opportunity, or change request.

SwarmMember.description: Represents a Salesforce member, such as an agent, of a swarm.

TabDefinition.description: Represents a custom tab. Returns only the tabs that the current user has access to.

TagCategory.description: Group similar interest tags together into tag categories.

TagDefinition.description: Defines the attributes of child Tag objects.

Task.description: Represents a business activity such as making a phone call or other to-do items. In the user interface, Task and Event records are collectively referred to as activities.

TaskPriority.description: Represents the importance or urgency of a task, such as High, Normal, or Low.

TaskRelation.description: Represents the relationship between a task and a lead, contacts, and other objects related to the task. If Shared Activities is enabled, this object doesn’t support triggers, workflow, or data validation rules.

TaskStatus.description: Represents the status of a task, such as Not Started, Completed, or Closed.

TaskTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a task .

TaskWhoRelation.description: Represents the relationship between a task and a lead or contacts.

TaxDisclosureSummary.description: Represents statistics about the disclosure of business entity information to all tax jurisdictions.

TaxEngine.description: A tax engine represents both an instance of a tax engine provider as well as the merchant credentials for that specific instance. When Subscription Management calculates tax on an order item, it sends a request through Subscription Management Tax Calculation API to an external tax engine. The Salesforce tax engine record contains information passed to the external tax engine, such as

TaxEngineInteractionLog.description: A record of a communication with an external tax engine following a tax calculation request.

TaxEngineProvider.description: Represents general information about a service that manages a tax engine, such as the ID of the tax adapter Apex class in Salesforce, and the engine’s namespace prefix. Tax engine providers have a one-to-many relationship with tax engines, where the tax engine record represents a specific configuration of a tax engine that can be assigned to multiple order items.

TaxGeoConfig.description: Represents a tax configuration associated with a GeoCountry.

TaxPolicy.description: A tax policy contains a group of tax treatments, where each treatment represents parameters to determine how a particular product is taxed for a transaction line item. Tax policies are related to products, which pass the policy on to the resulting order items. When you activate an order, Subscription Management assigns a tax treatment to each order item based on the tax policy's DefaultTaxTreatmentId, then uses the tax treatment to calculate tax.

TaxRate.description: Represents a tax rate for a tax code and country.

TaxTreatment.description: A tax treatment contains details about how Salesforce and external engines calculate taxes, and the tax engine to use for tax calculation. The IsTaxable field determines whether tax is calculated for the product in the transaction. The tax code, tax engine, and product code are sent via API to the external tax calculation service. When you invoice an order item that has a tax treatment, the invoice line inherits the tax treatment from the order item’s related billing schedule. The invoice line’s TaxCode field is populated based on the code that the tax engine used for calculation.

Team.description: Represents the team of members associated with an organization.

TeamMember.description: Represents the member associated with a team.

TelemetryActionDefStep.description: Represents a step in the action for a telemetry signal definition.

TelemetryActionDefinition.description: Represents the action taken on a telemetry signal sent from a connected asset or vehicle, such as getting the current status of a vehicle or its component, or sending a request to perform a remote action on the vehicle or its component.

TelemetryActionRelatedProcess.description: Represents the relationship between a telemetry action and a process triggered by the action such as a service catalog item definition or a product.

TelemetryActnDefStepAttr.description: Represents the attributes of a telemetry action definition step.

TelemetryDefinition.description: Represents the definition of the structure of a telemetry signal sent from a connected asset or vehicle.

TelemetryDefinitionVersion.description: Represents a version of the structure of a telemetry signal sent from a connected asset or vehicle.

TenantScrAIPrmptInjection.description: Stores generative AI prompt injection data.

TenantSecret.description: This object stores an encrypted organization-specific key fragment that’s used with the primary secret (KDF seed) to produce org-specific data encryption keys.

TenantSecurityAIGtwyUsage.description: Stores Einstein generative AI gateway usage data.

TenantSecurityAlertRuleSelectedTenant.description: Stores information about a Security Center alert rule for tenants.

TenantSecurityApiAnomaly.description: Stores detected anomalies in how users typically make API calls. Fore more information, see Threat Detection. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityCertificate.description: Stores metric details related to public key certificate information. The certificate binds the public key to the identity of an entity.

TenantSecurityConfigAgent.description: Stores metric details related to implemented Agentforce Agents

TenantSecurityCustomMetricSetup.description: Represents the configuration for a custom metric within Security Center.

TenantSecurityCustomMetricStat.description: Represents custom metric data within Security Center.

TenantSecurityEncryptedField.description: Represents fields encrypted under your Shield Platform Encryption policy.

TenantSecurityFeature.description: Stores org features across all tenants in Security Center.

TenantSecurityGuestUserAnomaly.description: Represents metric details for guest user anomaly events detected by Threat Detection.

TenantSecurityHealthCheckDetail.description: Stores the details of Health Check scores for a connected tenant. The Health Check detail page in Security Center displays scores and settings for all your tenants in one place. Use this object to get settings and risks per tenant on a selected date.

TenantSecurityHealthCheckTrend.description: Stores the history of Security Health Check scores for a connected tenant within Security Center. Health Check in Security Center displays Health Check scores and the average risk settings for all your tenants in one place. This object belongs to the parent tenant and stores Health Check data pushed from child tenants. This object is available for Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityLicense.description: Stores license usage information within Security Center.

TenantSecurityLogin.description: Stores the login details of a single user to a tenant, grouped by date and type. You can query this object to find out how many times the user logged in to a specific tenant using a specific login type (for example, username/password or SSO). This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityLoginIpRangeTrend.description: Stores details of changes related to login IP ranges in Security Center.

TenantSecurityMetricDetailLink.description: Represents the link between the metric count and metric drill down.

TenantSecurityMobilePolicyTrend.description: Stores metrics related to changes in mobile security policies across all tenants in Security Center.

TenantSecurityMonitorMetric.description: Stores the daily count and daily count change for a metric within Security Center. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityNotification.description: Stores information about notifications that were triggered in Security Center as a function of the Alerts feature. For more information, see Create Alerts for Security Changes.

TenantSecurityNotificationRule.description: Stores an alert configured in the Security Center Alerts feature to notify recipients of changes made to security settings. For more information, see Create Alerts for Security Changes. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityPolicy.description: Stores security policies created and deployed in Security Center. For more information, see Define and Deploy Security Policies.

TenantSecurityPolicyDeployment.description: Stores the status of deployments of a Security Center policy on a tenant. For more information, see Define and Deploy Security Policies. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 54.0 and later.

TenantSecurityPolicySelectedTenant.description: Stores the list of tenants selected for a Security Center policy. For more information, see Define and Deploy Security Policies. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 54.0 and later.

TenantSecurityReportAnomaly.description: Stores anomalies in how users run or export reports, including unsaved reports, as detected by Threat Detection. For more information, see Threat Detection. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityTenantInfo.description: Stores information on changes related to the tenant history.

TenantSecurityTransactionPolicyTrend.description: Stores changes to the count of Transaction Security Policies for a connected tenant within Security Center.

TenantSecurityTrigTransactionSecurityPol.description: Stores metric details related to Transaction Security Policy triggering events.

TenantSecurityTrustedIpRangeTrend.description: Stores details of changes related to trusted IP ranges in Security Center.

TenantUsageEntitlement.description: Represents a data structure that contains information about the features or functionalities that a Salesforce org has access to.

Term.description: Represents a term or condition applied for a loan application or a collateral.

TermRelatedObject.description: Represents the relationship between a term and the object for which the term is defined.

Territory.description: Represents a flexible collection of accounts and users where the users have at least read access to the accounts, regardless of who owns the accounts.

Territory2AlignmentLog.description: Represents the start and end status of a territory assignment rule run job.

Territory2ModelHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to the values in the fields on a territory model.

Territory2ObjSharingConfig.description: Represents the sharing access level of objects assigned to a particular territory.

Territory2ObjectExclusion.description: Represents the objects that aren’t included in territory assignment rule runs, even when they meet assignment rule criteria.

Territory2Type.description: Represents a category for territories (Territory2). Every Territory2 must have a Territory2Type.

TerritoryAdminAssignment.description: Represents designated team members who can administer specific territories and their descendants.

TerritoryMgmtObjectConfig.description: Represents territory management settings and defaults for a particular object.

TestSuiteMembership.description: Associates an Apex class with an ApexTestSuite.

ThirdPartyAccountLink.description: Represents the list of external users who authenticated using an authentication provider.

ThreatDetectionFeedback.description: Represents feedback provided by a user about a Threat Detection event that occurred in your org. The feedback specifies whether the event was malicious, suspicious, not a threat, or unknown. Each ThreatDetectionFeedback object is associated with one of these Threat Detection storage events: ApiAnomalyEventStore, CredentialStuffingEventStore, ReportAnomalyEventStore, or SessionHijackingEventStore.

Time-Based Workflow Event Type.description: Time-Based Workflow events contain details about queue activity monitoring.

TimePeriod.description: Represents the time period that's used to calculate the indicator performance and result.

TimeSheet.description: Represents a schedule of a service resource’s time in Field Service or Workforce Engagement.

TimeSheetEntry.description: Represents a span of time that a service resource spends on a field service task.

TimeSheetEntryItem.description: Represents the details of the time sheet entry that is used by an Enterprise Asset Management system to pay the field service worker accroding to labor laws and company policy.

TimeSheetValidationError.description: Represents validation errors in time sheets, time sheet entries, and time sheet entry items based on the rules defined by the admin.

TimeSheetWageTypeSummary.description: Represents a summary of the type of wages earned by a field service resource.

TimeSlot.description: Represents a period of time on a specified day of the week during which work can be performed in Salesforce Scheduler. Operating hours consist of one or more time slots.

TimeSlotHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a time slot.

TimelineObjectDefinitionLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a timeline configuration’s master label when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization.

TodayGoal.description: Sets the quarterly sales goal on the performance chart.

Topic.description: Represents a topic on a Chatter post or record.

TopicAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a topic to a specific feed item, record, or file.

TopicLocalization.description: Represents the translated version of a topic name. Topic localization applies only to navigational and featured topics in Experience Cloud sites.

TopicUserEvent.description: Represents an action (such as comment, post, like, or share) made by a user on a topic.

TrackedCommunication.description: Stores information request or communication details sent from payer to provider on a member’s authorization request.

TrackedCommunicationDetail.description: Stores additional information associated with TrackedCommunication records.

TrainingCourseParticipant.description: Represents the trainings completed by a person.

Transaction Security Event Type.description: Transaction Security events contain details about policy execution. This event type is supported in API version 55.0 and later.

TransactionSecurityEventLog.description: Transaction Security event logs contain details about policy execution. Legacy transaction security policy details are supported in API version 38.0 and later. Enhanced transaction security policy details are supported in API version 55.0 and later.

TransactionSecurityPolicy.description: Represents a transaction security policy definition.

Translation.description: The Translation object represents the languages enabled for translation in your Salesforce org.

TravelMode.description: Represents a travel mode used for travel time calculations. The records include information about the type of transportation (such as Car or Walking), whether a vehicle can take toll roads, and whether a vehicle is transporting hazardous materials.

TrnCourse.description: Represents information about the authorized trainings that qualify a license or permit.

TwoFactorInfo.description: Stores a user’s secret for multi-factor operations. Use this object when customizing multi-factor authentication in your organization. (Note that multi-factor authentication was formerly called two-factor authentication.)

TwoFactorMethodsInfo.description: Stores information about which identity verification methods a user has registered.

TwoFactorTempCode.description: Stores information about a user’s temporary verification code for confirming their identity when logging in.

UI Telemetry Navigation Timing Event Typ.file: objects/U/UI Telemetry Navigation Timing Event Type.json
UI Telemetry Navigation Timing Event Typ.description: UI Telemetry Navigation Timing events capture network performance metrics related to page navigation. The event extends from the UI Telemetry Resource Timing Event and includes requests initiated with either the Fetch API or the XMLHttpRequest API.

UI Telemetry Resource Timing Event.description: UI Telemetry Resource Timing events capture network performance metrics related to loading an application’s resources. The event includes requests initiated with either the Fetch API or the XMLHttpRequest API.

URI Event Type.description: URI events contain details about user interaction with the web browser UI.

UiAgentInteractionEventLog.description: This log tracks client side interactions and events with the Agentforce panel. It is limited to Salesforce Lightning Experience, Salesforce Mobile, and Conversation Preview within Agentforce Builder.

UiFormulaCriterion.description: Represents a filter that helps define component visibility on a Lightning page.

UiFormulaRule.description: Represents a set of one or more filters that define the conditions under which a component displays on a Lightning page.

UiTelemetryNavTmEventLog.description: UI Telemetry Navigation Timing events capture network performance metrics related to page navigation. The event extends from the UI Telemetry Resource Timing Event and includes requests initiated with either the Fetch API or the XMLHttpRequest API.

UiTelemetryRsrcTmEventLog.description: UI Telemetry Resource Timing events capture network performance metrics related to loading an application’s resources. The event includes requests initiated with either the Fetch API or the XMLHttpRequest API.

UndecidedEventRelation.description: Represents event participants (invitees or attendees) with the status Not Responded for a given event.

UnderwritingRule.description: Represents details of an underwriting rule for a product.

UnderwritingRuleGroup.description: Represents the underwriting rule that's associated with a product.

UnifiedActivity.description: Represents an activity that is automatically captured from Einstein Activity Capture (EAC) or other activity data, such as calls, manually logged tasks, and emails. This object consists of fields common to all types of activity-related objects such as Event, Task, EmailMessage, VoiceCall, VideoCall, and so on.

UnifiedActivityInsight.description: Represents an insight related to a unified activity.

UnifiedActivityParticipant.description: Represents a participant in an activity. For example, a participant in a voice call is someone who initiated the call or someone who received the call.

UnifiedActivityRelation.description: Represents a relationship between an activity and a related record that’s a target or topic of the activity. For example, a related record can be an opportunity, account, and so on.

UnifiedActvtyInsightKeyword.description: Represents a keyword in a communication that triggered the activity insight.

UnifiedEmail.description: Represents an email that was captured or synced from an EmailMessage or Task record.

UnifiedEmailParticipant.description: Represents a participant in an email.

UnifiedMeeting.description: Represents a meeting that was captured or synced from an Event record.

UnifiedMeetingParticipant.description: Represents a participant in a meeting.

UnifiedTask.description: Represents a business activity such as a to-do item.

UnifiedTaskParticipant.description: Represents a participant in a task.

UnifiedVideoCall.description: Represents a video call that is captured or synced from the VideoCall or Task record.

UnifiedVideoCallParticipant.description: Represents a participant in a video call.

UnifiedVoiceCall.description: Represents a voice call that is captured or synced from a VoiceCall or Task record.

UnifiedVoiceCallParticipant.description: Represents a participant in a voice call.

Unique Query Event Type.description: Unique Query events capture specific search queries (SOQL), filter IDs, and report IDs that are processed, along with the underlying database queries (SQL).

UniqueQueryEventLog.description: Unique Query events capture specific search queries (SOQL), filter IDs, and report IDs that are processed, along with the underlying database queries (SQL).

UnitOfMeasure.description: Represents the unit of measures for care metrics and care observations

UriEventLog.description: URI events contain details about user interaction with the web browser UI.

UsageImpactFactor.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up the Usage Impact Factors used across jurisdictions and programs.

UsageImpactGroup.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up the Usage Impact Groups used across jurisdictions and programs.

UsageImpactGroupFactor.description: Represents a junction between an Usage Impact Group version and Usage Impact Factor.

UsageImpactGroupPgmMeasure.description: Represents a junction between the program, product, and Usage Impact Group version.

UsageImpactGroupVersion.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up the versions of Usage Impact Groups.

User.description: Represents a user in your organization.

UserAccessChange.description: Represents a change related to user access.

UserAccountTeamMember.description: Represents a User on the default account team of another User.

UserAppInfo.description: Stores the last Lightning app logged in to. If the user hasn’t logged into Salesforce or if the user lost access to the last accessed app, the UserAppInfo object stores a Null value.

UserAppMenuCustomization.description: Represents an individual user’s settings for items in the app menu or App Launcher.

UserAppMenuItem.description: Represents the organization-wide settings for items in the app menu or App Launcher that the requesting user has access to in Setup.

UserAuthCertificate.description: Represents a user authentication certificate in your org. A user certificate is a unique PEM-encoded X.509 digital certificate to authenticate individual users to your org.

UserConfigTransferButton.description: Represents the association between a Chat configuration and a live chat button. This association allows users associated with a specific configuration to transfer chats to a button queue.

UserConfigTransferSkill.description: Represents the association between a Chat configuration and a skill. This association allows users associated with a specific configuration to transfer chats to agents who have that skill.

UserCustomBadge.description: Represents a custom badge for a user.

UserCustomBadgeLocalization.description: Represents the translated version of a custom badge for a user.

UserDailyMetric.description: Represents the daily engagement metrics for a user.

UserDailyMetricOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing the user daily metric with users other than the owner.

UserDefinedLabel.description: Represents a label created by a user to help organize, track, and find records.

UserDefinedLabelAssignment.description: Represents a relationship between a record label and the item the user assigned it to.

UserDevice.description: Represents information unique to a device.

UserDeviceApplication.description: Represents information on applications installed on a device that is accessing Salesforce.

UserDeviceHistory.description: Represents tracking information on the UserDevice sObject.

UserEmailCalendarSync.description: Represents the user assignments of an Einstein Activity Capture configuration.

UserEmailPreferredPerson.description: Represents a mapping for a user’s preferred record for an email address when multiple records match an email field.

UserEmailPreferredPersonShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a UserEmailPreferredPerson object. Sharing is not customizable for UserEmailPreferredPerson records.

UserFinancialAuthority.description: Represents the maximum monetary amount a user can authorize for a given financial type and product.

UserLicense.description: Represents a user license in your organization. A user license entitles a user to specific functionality and determines the profiles and permission sets available to the user.

UserListView.description: Represents the customizations a user made to a list view.

UserListViewCriterion.description: Represents the criterion for a user’s customized list view. The criterion consists of the filters or sort order a user added to a list view for the Salesforce Mobile app.

UserLocationAssignment.description: Represents the assignment between a location and a user.

UserLogin.description: Represents the settings that affect a user’s ability to log into an organization. To access this object, you need the UserPermissions.ManageUsers permission.

UserMembershipSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing user records from a source group to a target group. A user record contains details about a user. Users who are members of the source group can be shared with members of the target group. The source and target groups can be based on roles, portal roles, public groups, or territories.

UserMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for a user.

UserMonthlyMetricOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing the user monthly metric with users other than the owner.

UserPackageLicense.description: Represents a license for an installed managed package, assigned to a specific user.

UserPermissionAccess.description: Represents the permissions accessibility for a current user.

UserPreference.description: Represents a functional preference for a specific user in your organization.

UserPrioritizedRecord.description: Represents records that Pipeline Inspection, Account Intelligence, Contact Intelligence, and Lead Intelligence users flag as important for tracking in pipeline and intelligence views and filters.

UserProvAccount.description: Represents information that links a Salesforce user account with an account in a third-party (target) system, such as Google, for users of connected apps with Salesforce user provisioning enabled.

UserProvAccountStaging.description: Temporarily stores user account information while a user completes the User Provisioning Wizard. This information that is stored in the UserProvAccount object when you click the button to collect and analyze accounts on the target system.

UserProvMockTarget.description: Represents an entity for testing user data before committing the data to a third-party system for user provisioning.

UserProvisioningConfig.description: Represents information for a flow to use during a user provisioning request process, such as the attributes for an update.

UserProvisioningLog.description: Represents messages generated during the process of provisioning users for third-party applications.

UserProvisioningRequest.description: Represents an individual provisioning request to create, update, or delete a single user account in a third-party service system (or another Salesforce organization).

UserRecordAccess.description: Represents a user’s access to a set of records.

UserRole.description: Represents a user role in your organization.

UserServicePresence.description: Represents a presence user’s real-time presence status.

UserSetupEntityAccess.description: Represents the enabled custom permissions of the running user.

UserShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a user record.

UserTeamMember.description: Represents a single User on the default opportunity team of another User.

UserTerritory.description: Represents a User who has been assigned to a Territory.

UserTerritory2AssocLog.description: Represents a log of when a user is assigned and unassigned from a territory.

UserTerritory2Association.description: Represents an association (by assignment) between a territory and a user record.

UserUIPreference.description: Represents user preferences for Salesforce components.

UserWorkList.description: Represents a list of work items in the My List tab for Sales Engagement users.

UserWorkListItem.description: Represents an individual work item in the My List tab for Sales Engagement users.

VehicleAssetCrbnFtprnt.description: Represents the total carbon emissions from vehicles. Carbon footprint quantifies the effect of atmospheric warming, which is represented in metric tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e).

VehicleAssetEmssnSrc.description: Represents assets that are mobile in nature, use energy that can be recorded, and are the source of greenhouse gas emissions.

VehicleAssetEnrgyUse.description: Represents the fuel consumption related to vehicles.

VehicleDefinition.description: Represents information about a typical vehicle model.

VehicleSearchableField.description: Represents a common dataset including multiple fields and values from multiple objects and is used as the basis for inventory search related to vehicles.

VehicleUserAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a vehicle to a driver. Vehicle is a moving location.

VendorCallCenterStatusMap.description: Stores a mapping between a call center vendor agent status and a Salesforce presence status for an associated call center.

VendorProject.description: Represents information about a vendor's proejct for which the loan was applied.

VerificationHistory.description: Represents the past six months of your org users’ attempts to verify their identity.

VettingEvaluation.description: Represents the evaluation of a candidate based on a vetting procedure.

VideoCallParticipant.description: Represents a participant in a video call.

VideoCallRecording.description: Represents a recording from a video call, such as a video recording, a voice recording, or a transcript.

ViolationEnforcementAction.description: Represents the action that a regulatory authority takes to address violations.

ViolationType.description: Represents violations types for licenses and permits.

ViolationTypeAssessmentInd.description: Represents violation types associated with assessment indicator definitions.

ViolationTypeUse.description: Represents a junction between a set of assessment questions and the violation type associated with them.

Visit.description: Represents a visit to inspect, assess compliance, or assess an applicant’s ability to get a license or permit or inspect.

VisitedParty.description: Represents the contact person at the account that’s being visited.

VisitedPartyFeed.description: This object represents the posts and feed-tracked changes of the VisitedParty object.

Visitor.description: Represents the inspectors performing inspection visits.

VisitorFeed.description: This object represents the posts and feed-tracked changes of the Visitor object.

Visualforce Request Event Type.description: Visualforce Request events contain details of Visualforce requests. Requests can originate from the browser (UI).

VisualforceAccessMetrics.description: Represents summary statistics for Visualforce pages.

VisualforceRequestEventLog.description: Visualforce Request events contain details of Visualforce requests. Requests can originate from the browser (UI).

VoiceCall.description: Represents a call in Service Cloud Voice, Sales Dialer, or other supported voice connectors. For Service Cloud Voice, this can be a phone or Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) call. This object is available in API version 40.0 and later.

VoiceCallList.description: Represents a prioritized list of numbers to call.

VoiceCallListItem.description: Represents a single phone number in a prioritized call list.

VoiceCallMetrics.description: Represents metrics for a VoiceCall lifecycle event, aggregated daily.

VoiceCallQualityFeedback.description: Represents feedback given by a Sales Dialer user about the quality of a VoiceCall .

VoiceCallRecording.description: Represents a call recording in Service Cloud Voice and Sales Dialer.

VoiceCoaching.description: Represents a call that is using call monitoring.

VoiceLocalPresenceNumber.description: Represents a phone number with the same area code as the person who’s being called.

VoiceMailContent.description: Represents a voicemail message left by a caller to the context user.

VoiceMailGreeting.description: Represents a custom greeting message that plays upon reaching a user’s voicemail.

VoiceOrgSetting.description: Represents the org's customized voice settings.

VoiceUserLine.description: Represents a user’s forwarding phone number.

VoiceUserPreferences.description: Represents the number the user displays when making outbound calls.

VoiceVendorInfo.description: Represents information about the Service Cloud Voice or Sales Dialer provider’s vendor.

VoiceVendorLine.description: Represents a user’s phone number reserved with the vendor.

VolunteerProject.description: Represents information about activities that must be carried out within a certain time frame, at a specified location, by one or more volunteers.

Vote.description: Represents a vote that a user has made on a Knowledge Article, Idea, or Reply.

Voucher.description: Represents details about a voucher that's issued to a loyalty program member.

VoucherDefinition.description: Represents details about a voucher definition that’s associated with a loyalty program.

Waitlist.description: Represents a queue to which drop in customers who visit the branch without an already scheduled appointment are added.

WaitlistParticipant.description: Represents a customer who is added to a waitlist.

WaitlistServiceResource.description: Represents the relationship between the Waitlist object and the Service Resource object for Salesforce Scheduler.

WaitlistWorkType.description: Represents the relationship between the Waitlist object and the Work Type object for Salesforce Scheduler.

WarrantyTerm.description: Represents warranty terms defining the labor, parts, and expenses covered, along with any exchange options, provided to rectify issues with products.

WarrantyTermCoverage.description: Represents a junction between the warranty term coverage and a product or codeset, such as the repair code or labor code.

WasteFootprint.description: Represents the volume of aggregated waste and carbon emissions from waste generated either as part of operations or during the end- of- life of a product.

WasteFootprintItem.description: Represents the volume by waste type and disposal type of aggregated waste generated either as part of operations or during the end- of- life of a product.

WatchlistedLearner.description: Represents information for a learner that needs to be monitored for support.

Wave Change Event Type.description: Wave Change events represent route or page changes made in the CRM Analytics user interface. A Wave Change event type is captured every time the user opens a new CRM Analytics asset or tab, switches between tabs, or changes dashboard pages. Wave Change events are logged when opening new tabs and switching back to previously opened tabs.

Wave Download Event Type.description: represent downloads made from lens explorations and dashboard widgets in the CRM Analytics user interface. A Wave Download event type is captured when a user downloads images ( .png ), Microsoft® Excel® data ( .xls ), or comma-separated values ( .csv ) files.

Wave Interaction Event Type.description: Wave Interaction events represent route or page changes made in the CRM Analytics user interface. A Wave Interaction event type is captured when a tab is closed. It also collates the interaction statistics over the life of the tab, including total open time, read time, and so on. These statistics are aggregated as you go to other tabs and return, and logged only once when the tab is closed.

Wave Performance Event Type.description: Wave Performance events help you track trends in your Analytics performance.

WaveAutoInstallRequest.description: Provides access to the concrete object that represents a CRM Analytics auto-install request. The auto-install request tracks the progress of CRM Analytics applications created from CRM Analytics templates by the automated process user.

WealthAppConfig.description: Represents configuration information for Financial Services Cloud functionality.

WebCart.description: Represents an online shopping cart for a store built with B2B Commerce or D2C Commerce, with total amounts for products, shipping and handling, and taxes.

WebCartAdjustmentBasis.description: Coupons that trigger promotions for the cart. When a customer tries to add a coupon to the cart, the store looks for promotions associated with the coupon. If a promotion results in a price adjustment, a WebCartAdjusmentBasis record is created.

WebCartAdjustmentGroup.description: Group of price adjustments for a cart.

WebCartHistory.description: WebCartHistory represents the history of changes to the values in the fields of the WebCart object.

WebLink.description: Represents a custom link to a URL or Scontrol.

WebLinkLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of the field label for a custom link to a URL or s-control when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization.

WebStore.description: Represents a B2B or D2C store.

WebStoreCatalog.description: Represents the collection of products associated with a store.

WebStoreInventorySource.description: Used to configure the inventory source for a webstore.

WebStoreMessageContent.description: Represents the assocation of a managed content message record in CMS to a web store, along with other attributes that specify the application and intent of the message content.

WebStoreNetwork.description: Represents the relationship between a web store and an experience site.

WebStorePricebook.description: Represents a store price book used in Lightning B2B Commerce.

WebStoreSearchProdSettings.description: Search settings for a WebStore product search.

WebStoreShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a B2B or D2C store.

WebstoreBuyerGroup.description: Associates a webstore with a buyer group. Supports dynamically changing locales when buyers shop in orgs that are enabled for multiple languages and currencies.

Wishlist.description: Represents a buyer-created list of WishlistItems in a store that’s built with B2B Commerce on Lightning.

WishlistItem.description: Represents an item on a Wishlist in a store built with B2B Commerce for Lightning.

WorkAccess.description: Used to grant or restrict user access to give badge definitions. Each badge definition record must have one WorkAccess record.

WorkAccessShare.description: Used to control Givers of WorkBadgeDefinition records.

WorkBadge.description: Represents information about who the badge was given to and which badge was given. A WorkBadge record is created for each recipient of a WorkBadgeDefinition.

WorkBadgeDefinition.description: Represents the attributes of a badge including the badge name, description, and image. Each WorkBadge record must have a lookup to a WorkBadgeDefinition since badge attributes (like badge name) are derived from the WorkBadgeDefinition object.

WorkCapacityAvailability.description: Represents the available work capacity for a specific time and service territory.

WorkCapacityLimit.description: Represents the capacity limit in a specific service territory for a workstream or for the whole service territory in a given period.

WorkCapacityUsage.description: Represents the capacity usage in a specific service territory for a workstream or for the whole service territory in a given period.

WorkCoaching.description: Represents a single coaching relationship between two users. One of the users is defined as the coach and the other is defined as a coachee. WorkCoaching is feed-enabled so there is a private feed available to the coach and coachee.

WorkDemographic.description: Represents the field values used to specify slices in the workload forecasting and capacity planning.

WorkFeedback.description: Represents the answer to a question that a person was asked via a feedback request. Also used to store offered feedback without linking it to a particular question.

WorkFeedbackQuestion.description: Represents a free-form text type or multiple choice question within a set of questions.

WorkFeedbackQuestionSet.description: Represents a set of questions being asked. The question set is used to link all the individual requests where different recipients were asked the same set of questions on the same subject.

WorkFeedbackRequest.description: Represents a single feedback request on a subject or topic (question) to a single recipient in the feedback application. In the case of offered feedback, WorkFeedbackRequest represents feedback that is offered about a subject. In the performance application, WorkFeedbackRequest represents a request for feedback on a set of questions from a question set, on a subject—for the recipient to complete and submit.

WorkGoal.description: Represents the components of a goal, such as its description and associated metrics.

WorkGoalCollaborator.description: Represents collaborators on a WorkGoal object. This doesn’t include WorkGoal followers, which is handled by Chatter Feed Follow functionality.

WorkGoalCollaboratorHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to the values in the fields in a WorkGoalCollaborator object. Access is read-only.

WorkGoalHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to the values in the fields of a WorkGoal. Access is read-only.

WorkGoalLink.description: Represents the relationship between two goals (many to many relationship).

WorkGoalShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a WorkGoal object.

WorkOrder.description: Represents field service work to be performed for a customer.

WorkOrderHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a work order.

WorkOrderLineItem.description: Represents a subtask on a work order in field service.

WorkOrderLineItemHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a work order line item.

WorkOrderLineItemStatus.description: Represents a possible status of a work order line item in field service.

WorkOrderShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a work order.

WorkOrderStatus.description: Represents a possible status of a work order in field service.

WorkPerformanceCycle.description: Represents feedback that is gathered to assess the performance of a specific set of employees.

WorkPlan.description: Represents a work plan for a work order or work order line item.

WorkPlanSelectionRule.description: Represents a rule that selects a work plan for a work order or work order line item.

WorkPlanTemplate.description: Represents a template for a work plan.

WorkPlanTemplateEntry.description: Represents an object that associates a work step template with a work plan template.

WorkProcedure.description: Represent information about a procedure or process that's part of a program, such as a care program in Health Cloud or Life Sciences Cloud.

WorkProcedureStep.description: Represent information about the work type that's a part of a work procedure.

WorkReport.description: Represents the total work performed by a contractor business in a certain period of time for utility customers at one or more locations, providing services for one or more measures.

WorkReportError.description: Represents errors in the Work Report through the Work Report Line Item object.

WorkReportLineItem.description: Represents one measure of work performed by a contractor business for a consumer at a location within a program.

WorkReward.description: Used to store reward codes tied to a Reward Fund. Reward Funds must have at least one WorkReward record.

WorkRewardFund.description: Represents a Reward Fund and describes the Reward Fund attributes.

WorkRewardFundType.description: Represents the type of WorkRewardFund object.

WorkStep.description: Represents a work step in a work plan.

WorkStepStatus.description: Represents a picklist for a status category on a work step.

WorkStepTemplate.description: Represents a template for a work step.

WorkThanks.description: Represents the source and message of a thanks post.

WorkType.description: Represents a type of work to be performed in Salesforce Scheduler.
